        "text": "Instead, Maelle uses Sword Balletor Stendhal to deal devastating single-target damage, and the Painted Power Lumina is crucial here to allow Maelle to exceed the 9,999 limit on every hit.\n\nIn this DPS Maelle build, she enters the Virtuose Stance to deal damage, but this time she doesn\u2019t use Percee. Instead, Maelle uses Sword Balletor Stendhal to deal devastating single-target damage, and the Painted Power Lumina is crucial here to allow Maelle to exceed the 9,999 limit on every hit. Players can still use Percee when there\u2019s not enough AP, or even replace it with Momentum Strike, which is an upgraded skill with the same effect, but much more damage. It's best to have teammates that can apply Burn so that she doesn't need to use Spark. Guard Down stays important since it puts Maelle in a position where she allows her team to deal damage as well. That\u2019s important because Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 endgame is filled with monsters that absorb so much damage. Spark is also very supportive and must stay in her kit since most of the game\u2019s strategy revolves around the Burn DoT.\n\nMaelle in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 is an excellent early game DPS that can also work as a support later on; here's how to build Maelle.\n\nClair Obscur: Expedition 33 is a turn-based RPG game that focuses on teamwork during combat. Each character has a wide variety of skills that enable them to take any role. Of course, players choose these roles by building the characters accordingly. When it comes to Maelle in Expedition 33, most of her skills focus on hitting and debuffing one enemy, which lowers her value in AoE fights. However, against bosses, Maelle shines and showcases how important she can be for the team if her build supports that. So, here are the best builds for Maelle in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. Updated on December 13, 2025, by Nahda Nabiilah: Maelle is one of the most versatile characters in Expedition 33 when it comes to combat. She can smoothly shift from top-tier support to a damage dealer that melts anything in her path. As players unlock more weapons and Pictos, her build options continue to expand.\n\nEarly in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, Maelle is a great hybrid damage dealer with her one-shot skills and her supportive abilities. Here\u2019s the best early game build for Maelle in Expedition 33: Starting from Maelle\u2019s stats, players must build as much Speed and Critical Rate as possible through her Pictos. She needs around 300 to 400 Speed, alongside 25% to 35% Crit Rate. This will help maximize Maelle\u2019s early game damage. Maelle will get an extra 25% Critical chance from her Critical Burn Lumina, which increases her Critical chance to reach around 50%. It\u2019s enough for an early game Maelle build. Start the fight by applying Burn on one enemy, using Maelle\u2019s Spark. After applying burn, cast Swift Stride on Maelle\u2019s next action to switch into Virtuose Stance. Now, she\u2019s ready to unleash Percee and deals 9999 damage in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33.",
