        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Here are some key strategies for dominating the toughest encounters: Use multi-hit skills like Fleuret Fury to quickly break through armor layers. Apply burn early with Spark to stack damage over time and soften up tough targets.\n\nHome \u00bb Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u00bb Guides \u00bb Maelle Build Guide \u2013 Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies | Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u00b7 Master Maelle in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 with the ultimate build guide. Learn how to dominate bosses using burst rotations, stance mechanics, and critical scaling. ... Use this guide to plan Maelle\u2019s build progression from start to finish \u2014 from her early fire-based crit combos all the way to late-game one-turn boss kills. Below are summaries of each section with key highlights. Find the best tips, guides, and strategies for Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 below: Ultimate Monoco Build Guide (Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies) Ultimate Verso Build Guide (Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies) Lune Build Guide \u2013 Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies \u00b7 Ultimate Gustave Build Guide (Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies) Ultimate Sciel Build Guide (Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies) ...\n\nUltimate Maelle build guide for Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. Best skills, weapons, and tactics to burst bosses and scale critical damage.\n\nSingle-Turn Boss Kills: Combined with Pictos like Painted Power and Critical Moment, Maelle can one-turn kill bosses using Stendhal and Phantom Strike in high-stakes setups. ... In the early stages of Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, Maelle\u2019s power comes from quickly entering Virtuose Stance and leveraging powerful multi-hit skills. Focus on maximizing her crit rate and agility for fast, high-damage strikes, and use her stance mechanics to stack damage bonuses. Strengths: High burst potential, rapid stance activation, powerful single-target damage, strong critical scaling. Weaknesses: Vulnerable if caught outside of Virtuose Stance, relies heavily on crits, and can struggle against high-defense enemies without proper setup. Spark \u2013 Low-cost fire skill that applies burn, essential for early game damage setups. Swift Stride \u2013 Quickly re-enters Virtuose Stance, key for maintaining burst cycles.\n\nMaelle (Solo DPS): Built for maximum solo burst with Pictos like Solo Fighter and Painted Power. Two Placeholder Allies: Use characters with low investment to trigger break setups or provide support as needed. Boss fights in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 often require careful planning and execution. Here are some key strategies for dominating the toughest encounters: Use multi-hit skills like Fleuret Fury to quickly break through armor layers. Apply burn early with Spark to stack damage over time and soften up tough targets. Save your highest damage abilities for moments when the boss is stunned to maximize burst potential. Leverage the armor-shredding power of the Barrier Breaker to quickly weaken high-defense enemies. Focus on maintaining high agility to act before the enemy and control the flow of battle. Use skills like Swift Stride to reposition and avoid incoming attacks.",
