        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Phantom Strike is ideal for clearing out groups, hitting all enemies multiple times with heavy Void damage. Against bosses and elite enemies, it makes a great opener for getting rid of minions.\n\nMaelle is Clair Obscur's ultimate damage-dealer by the end of the game.\n\nMaelle fights with precision and lots of fire in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. ... Between her unbelievable Skills, top-tier weapons, and the array of Luminas available to the entire team, you can set up Maelle to deal millions of damage in a turn, making her a threat to even the most dangerous bosses in Clair Obscur. Here's our favorite build for the lethal fencer. Maelle has access to arguably the best weapon in the game, so you should try to get it as soon as you can in Act 3 and level it up as high as possible. Lithum, a Void-elemental rapier, is earned by climbing the makeshift tower of The Reacher west of Visages' Island and defeating Alicia in a duel at the top. Maelle has to fight Alicia alone, and her opponent doesn't hold back, so it's a good idea to set her up with Luminas like Solo Fighter and Recovery before approaching the summit. Lithum scales best with Luck and Agility, so focus on maximizing those Attributes before distributing points elsewhere.\n\nIt can be a good idea to have other party members set up Marks for Maelle to exploit. Monoco's Chapelier Slash applies Mark to the entire enemy team, making it a good choice for this. ... These Pictos and their Luminas are practically must-haves in Clair Obscur. ... Even if you aggressively level up for Skill Points, Maelle's best powers remain locked until Act 3. Once she has them, though, she can tear through most standard encounters on her own. Phantom Strike is ideal for clearing out groups, hitting all enemies multiple times with heavy Void damage. Against bosses and elite enemies, it makes a great opener for getting rid of minions. Against single targets, it's best to open with Pyrolyse for high damage and several Burn stacks, then follow up with Burning Canvas for even more. If you can use a counter to switch to Virtuose Stance between turns, so much the better.\n\nSince Lithum lets Maelle exploit Marks without removing them, and Gustave's Homage gets more benefit from hitting Marked Targets, Rewarding Mark is a good way to help defray the Skill's high AP cost. Healing Parry helps keep Maelle at full Health, keeping Full Strength in play and saving the rest of the party from having to spend their turns keeping your damage-dealer alive. ... Finding Sastro's Lost Gestrals in Clair Obscur is a scavenger hunt that takes the entire game to complete.",
