        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Swift Stride \u2013 mobility skill that enhances tempo and lets Maelle reposition while maintaining pressure. Perc\u00e9e \u2013 strong single-target thrust, great for early boss damage. Spark \u2013 fast, low-cost damage option to keep flow between bigger nukes.\n\nSwift Stride \u2013 mobility skill that enhances tempo and lets Maelle reposition while maintaining pressure. Perc\u00e9e \u2013 strong single-target thrust, great for early boss damage. Spark \u2013 fast, low-cost damage option to keep flow between bigger nukes. The remaining slots are flexible. Momentum Strike \u2013 extends her damage cycles, keeping output steady during longer fights. Breaking Rules \u2013 reliable for shield breaks or bypassing high-defense enemies. Stendhal \u2013 core nuke; devastating damage when used in Virtuoso Stance. Last Chance \u2013 restores or maintains Virtuoso Stance, essential for consistency. Payback \u2013 high-damage counter skill, excellent after parries. Sword Ballet \u2013 crit-heavy burst option, devastating in endgame DPS phases. Immaculate \u2013 maximizes damage at full HP. Glass Cannon \u2013 trades defense for massive offensive scaling.\n\nThis setup turns Maelle into a high-damage burst DPS, specializing in first-turn nukes and maximizing critical output through Virtuoso Stance. With the right Weapon, Skills, Pictos & Luminas, she can shred bosses or clear waves before enemies have a chance to act. Maelle benefits from a mix of speed, durability, and crit scaling. Early investment into Crit/Luck helps her damage, while her final setup focuses on sustaining Virtuoso Stance and striking first. Agility \u2013 top priority to act first and set up burst turns. Defense \u2013 secondary investment to handle counterattacks and stay alive in glass-cannon builds. Luck (Crit) / Might \u2013 boosts raw damage and crit scaling for her nukes. The build revolves around enabling Virtuoso Stance as quickly as possible while maximizing damage scaling. Medalum \u2013 best-in-slot. Starts fights in Virtuoso Stance, boosting her damage from turn one.\n\nMaelle\u2019s playstyle focuses on entering Virtuoso Stance immediately and chaining high-crit nukes while managing AP. Start fights with First Strike and unleash Stendhal or Sword Ballet for massive damage. Use Last Chance if Virtuoso Stance is lost to maintain consistency. Parry when possible to trigger Payback and generate AP via Energizing Parry. Rotate between nukes and stance maintenance while leveraging buffs from Pictos and Luminas to maximize each burst phase. This setup makes Maelle a top-tier burst DPS, capable of deleting high-priority targets in one or two turns.",
