        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "This way, you can choose between Impulse Strike, Phantom Thrust, and Retribution, depending on which attack is most suitable for your situation. Therefore, it is especially designed for Act 2 and 3, when you become more familiar with countering.\n\nIn Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 there are several builds that you can use for Maelle. MeinMMO shows you 2 builds that make the challenging game easier. Update from December 16th: We have checked the article for relevance and made structural adjustments. How is this list structured? In this list, we outline possible builds for Maelle that you can build upon. Ultimately, your playstyle determines which builds are suitable for you. We do not present \u201cthe best\u201d build but rather provide several optimal options. ... Additionally, we explain how Maelle fundamentally works. This way, you can get the best out of the fighter. Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u2013 JRPG with French Flair has Release Date ...\n\nAdditionally, you can apply shields to Maelle beforehand and use Shield Affinity to increase damage by 30%. ... Deine Meinung? Diskutiere mit uns! ... This is an AI-powered translation. Some inaccuracies might exist. ... Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 is a turn-based role-playing game that gains a unique touch through real-time elements.\n\nWhat kind of build is this? This build is designed so that Maelle can spread the burning status to enemies by shooting. This way, she does not have to rely on other team members and can completely ignore the left side of her skill tree. She shoots and can alternate between Perc\u00e9e and Quick Step depending on the enemy\u2019s status. The build is particularly suitable in Act 1 of the game. ... Suitable weapon: The best weapon for the build is Medalum. The sword exploits that Maelle can spread the burning status. The status lasts longer and deals double damage. You receive the sword as a prize in the tournament in the village of the Gestrale when you complete the final challenge with Maelle. ... Special features of the build: By using the applied Pictos and Lumina, you can mark enemies with simple shots and put them in the burning status. This saves one round in which she would have to use a fire attack to set the enemy on fire.\n\nWith this build, you can ignore the left side of Maelle\u2019s skill tree. What kind of build is this? This build relies heavily on countering. You remain permanently in the virtuoso stance after you have parried an attack. This way, you can choose between Impulse Strike, Phantom Thrust, and Retribution, depending on which attack is most suitable for your situation. Therefore, it is especially designed for Act 2 and 3, when you become more familiar with countering. ... Suitable weapon: The perfect weapon for the counter build is Jarum. The rapier allows you to switch to the virtuoso stance after a counterattack. This way, you can use strong attacks without switching to the defensive stance, thus maintaining your damage bonus of 200%. ... Special features of the build: The applied Pictos and Lumina increase the damage you deal with counters and additionally give you more AP.",
