          "site_name": "GameSpot"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Early on skills like Rain of Fire, Perce and Fleuret Fury may all be useful to varying degrees but later as you gain access to Stenshal, Burning Canvas, Pyrolyse, Sword Ballet and her final Gradient attacks, you&#x27;ll notice very quickly she is made to deal damage.\n\nMaelle is the most effective damage dealer in the party and specializes in Burn damage and later Void damage as well. She is a fencer whose attack power and skills change depending on her stance. Everytime she uses a skill the skill will change her to a different stance (if she is in the stance already she will be changed to stanceless which is normal with no buffs or debuffs). She has 3 stances she is constantly switching between between skills, each providing different effect. Defensive Stance: Takes 50% less damage and she gains 1 Ap per parry and or dodge. Offensive Stance: She deals 50% more damage but also takes 50% more damage. Virtuoso Stance: Her best stance, where she deals 200% more damage. As she changes stances she also gets an extra AP. When using Base attacks in Offensive or Defensive she swaps to the opposite stance unless she has a weapon which states otherwise.\n\nMaelle is going to be the core damage dealer and most useful party member throughout the game, not only is her Burn damage incredibly effective against most enemies, her ability to deal 200% damage make her a might boss killer. In Act 1 and 2 she can be treated like an All rounded making use of both her damage dealing and buffs. However, when you reach Act 3 her potential becomes even greater, to the point she outshines all others in terms of damage. Early on skills like Rain of Fire, Perce and Fleuret Fury may all be useful to varying degrees but later as you gain access to Stenshal, Burning Canvas, Pyrolyse, Sword Ballet and her final Gradient attacks, you'll notice very quickly she is made to deal damage. Weapon wise you can obtain her best weapon as early as Act 1 and it can carry her for the entire game, Medallum, its passives only become better as you level it up.",
