        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Verso&#x27;s skills revolve around getting to Rank S as fast as possible. Start fights off with Quick Strike to quickly jump to Rank B. Afterward, use Assault Zero until you reach Rank A. Lastly, use Light Holder to recover AP and jump to Rank S ...\n\nVerso is a playable character who uses the Sword and Dagger in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. See Verso's best builds, weapon, attributes, playstyle, skills, and character profile here! ... The values in red are the ones to be prioritized. Act 2 is calculated with 90 points at level 30. Act 3 is calculated with 180 points at level 60. Verso does well when he has high Agility as it allows him to act more frequently while increasing his damage thanks to the scaling of some of his strong weapons. After putting points into Agility, invest in Luck for a higher Critical Hit rate, plus some other increases to his stats. This leveling strategy carries over to Act 3, with you ideally getting his Agility to 99. Once his Agility is 99, dump all of the other points into Luck for even more Critical Rate and weapon damage. Once both Agility and Luck are at 99, you can distribute the points however you want.\n\nVerso's skills revolve around getting to Rank S as fast as possible. Start fights off with Quick Strike to quickly jump to Rank B. Afterward, use Assault Zero until you reach Rank A. Lastly, use Light Holder to recover AP and jump to Rank S after finishing the attack. Once there, you can keep performing Defiant Strike to deal a lot of damage to the enemy while also applying a Mark on the enemy that his teammates can take advantage of. Should you need AP or HP, you can then use Paradigm Shift and Perfect Recovery respectively. In Act 3, however, you won't need to build up your Rank to S thanks to Chevalam's Passive Skill. Instead, you can immediately start dealing damage. If you are against multiple enemies, use Phantom Stars to deal a lot of AoE damage. Alternatively, you can replace Phantom Stars with Perfect Break since it can also break, but deals very high single-target damage.\n\nVerso's Picto choices revolve around giving him as much Speed and Critical Rate as possible, while still giving him strong Passive skills. As for Luminas, these help increase Verso's damage output and give him decent Survivability and AP recovery. Luminas like Augmented First Strike, Staggering Attack, and Breaker help Verso Break enemies and defeat them. Energising Start II, Energising Break, and Dead Energy help with his AP upkeep. If you are confident in your parrying, you can change some Luminas with Energising Parry and Perilous Parry for even more AP upkeep. Lastly, Healing Parry helps give Verso sustain, as you are forced to parry a lot with him anyway. The equipped Pictos give Verso strong passives, while also giving him Critical Rate, Health, and Speed. The Lumina themselves revolve around strengthening Verso's parries as much as possible, as well as increasing his damage output even with the downsides.\n\nThis team is still usable in Act 3, however the gameplay will slightly change. Verso will be sacrificing Powerful and Perfect Recovery for strong offensive moves like Ascending Assault and Phantom Stars, pushing his DPS capabilities to its limit. Lune will be handling all of the supporting with her heals and debuffs, with Maelle dealing her own large amounts of damage. Verso can still apply Marks for Maelle with Defiant Strike, as Maelle has access to even stronger skills at this point in the game. Make sure to parry and dodge well with Verso, as this build and team does turn him into a literal glass cannon. ... When playing Verso, try to get to S Rank as soon as possible. Being at S Rank gives you the highest damage increase, making your attacks hit harder than ever before. It is necessary to learn how to parry and dodge attacks with Verso as this is the easiest way to build and maintain your Perfection Rank.",
