        "type": "knowledge",
        "title": "Endgame Burn Stacking Build (Expert and NG+) - Clair Obscur Expedition 33",
        "url": "https://maxroll.gg/clair-obscur-expedition-33/guides/endgame-burn-stacking-build-expert-and-ng",
        "metadata": {
          "type": "webpage_metadata",
          "site_domain": "maxroll.gg",
          "favicon_url": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=maxroll.gg",
          "site_name": "Maxroll.gg"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Because Verso&#x27;s build uses the most Lumina points, Cheater is quite nice here. You can replace Fueling Break with any Pictos that gets Verso&#x27;s Critical Hit chance to 75%+. ... Verso&#x27;s most important Luminas are all related to inflicting burn ...\n\nBecause Verso's build uses the most Lumina points, Cheater is quite nice here. You can replace Fueling Break with any Pictos that gets Verso's Critical Hit chance to 75%+. ... Verso's most important Luminas are all related to inflicting burn and getting AP back to inflict more burn stacks on enemies. This is the \"burn stack\" portion of the build that gives it its namesake. The additional Luminas enable his ability to deal damage. Thanks to Sniper your first Free Aim Shot can break enemies, remember this and don't waste it. You can't nuke a boss out of nowhere with this setup, the way Maelle can, but between the repeated damage from Free Aim Shot and Attack, you can significantly lower an enemy's health and then finish them off with the burn tick when their turn starts. Longer Burn is not used because enemies do not survive long enough for this to matter.\n\nYou need to control the order in which your party acts during the first strike turn. This is done by changing the order in which you add members to the party and/or by adjusting their speed. The following turn orders are optimal: For single tanky enemies like bosses - Verso > Sciel > Maelle. This way Verso can stack burns on the target, then Sciel can buff Maelle with double damage and give Verso a second turn. Then, Maelle can nuke the enemy. If you don't have the damage to kill them before they get a turn because you're missing levels/weapon levels or Luminas, use the \"group\" setup below instead. For groups of 2-3 dangerous foes - Verso > Maelle > Sciel. With this setup, Verso still stacks burns, but now splits them between multiple targets. Maelle nukes the first boss, then re-enters Virtuose stance. After that, Sciel gives her double damage and a second turn to deal with the next boss.\n\nOnce you reach (and clear) Verso's Drafts, you obtain Esqium. This weapon consumes AP to provide a massive damage boost making it the build's best in slot weapon. However it does restrict your skill use significantly. Most of the time, you rotate between Burning Canvas to delete an enemy and Swift Stride to get back into Virtuose stance. Reverse this order if you're not starting in Virtuose stance. You can also use Fleuret Fury to break a powerful foe (doubling their burn) or take out a weaker enemy while remaining in Virtuose stance. Occasionally, Phantom Strike is useful for building into her level 3 Gradient, Spoiler Gradient Attack, which hits about as hard as Burning Canvas and Breaking Rules can delete enemy shields. ... AP Discount lowers your AP cost to 4 on Burning Canvas. Grab Energising Turn for more AP regen while you're at it. If you want to continue using Phantom Strike for AoE you need to use effects like Rewarding Mark and Energising Burn to generate AP during your turn\n\nMaelle's Luminas are all about using Auto Death with Survivor to set her health to 1 at the battle start and activate as many damage bonuses as possible. You can substitute other AP gain Pictos for Energy Master, such as Energising Turn and Energising Burn. If you need extra Critical Strike Chance and want to shift your Pictos to more Speed, use Critical Moment. ... Do not use Shortcut! This can disrupt your normal turn order and prevent Verso from playing before Maelle. ... Sciel's job is to make sure Maelle and Verso play as frequently as possible and double Maelle's damage to set up for a nuke. As such, she is primarily rotating between support skills while passively debuffing the enemy. The build also has an Auto Death swap that changes Sciel's turn order, inflicts a few burn stacks on all enemies, and adds +3 shields to both Verso and Maelle.",
