          "favicon_url": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=keengamer.com",
          "site_name": "KeenGamer"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Steeled Strike \u2013 Thirteen-hit skill for maximum multi-hit scaling, perfect for stacking perfection rapidly. Contorso \u2013 Lightning strike on critical hits, triggers additional hits for massive multi-hit scaling.\n\nHome \u00bb Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u00bb Guides \u00bb Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u2013 Ultimate Verso Build Guide (Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies) Master Verso in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 with this complete guide. Learn the best builds, weapons, skills, pictos, and advanced strategies to dominate every encounter. ... Verso is one of the most explosive and high-risk characters in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, known for his high burst damage, rapid perfection scaling, and multi-hit potential. If you want to break damage caps, overwhelm bosses, and unleash devastating single-target finishers, this guide will help you unlock his full potential. We\u2019ll cover the best builds from early to late game, including optimal skills, weapons, pictos, and advanced strategies to ensure you\u2019re always dealing top-tier damage. Mastering Verso\u2019s perfection rank system and critical hit potential will turn him into one of the deadliest characters in the game.\n\nBoss fights in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 often require careful planning and execution. Here are some key strategies for dominating the toughest encounters: Use multi-hit skills like Steeled Strike to quickly break through armor layers. Apply burn early with free aim shots to stack damage over time and soften up tough targets. Save your highest damage abilities for moments when the boss is stunned to maximize burst potential. Leverage the armor-shredding power of the Barrier Breaker to quickly weaken high-defense enemies. Focus on maintaining high agility to act before the enemy and control the flow of battle. Use skills like Speed Burst to reposition and avoid incoming attacks. Consider equipping Cheater to gain extra turns and maintain pressure. Use multi-hit skills like Steeled Strike to disrupt faster enemies and fill break bars quickly. Stack critical hit bonuses from Critical Moment and Painted Power for devastating one-turn setups.\n\nFinish with Steeled Strike for extreme burst potential against high-value targets. With this setup, Verso can rapidly scale to S rank in the mid-game, leveraging multi-hit attacks, critical setups, and aggressive AP management to dominate even the toughest encounters. In the next section, we will cover late-game builds, including the best endgame skills, weapons, and pictos for reaching maximum damage potential. ... In the late game, Verso reaches his full potential as a devastating one-man army capable of breaking damage caps and soloing the toughest bosses. At this stage, the focus shifts to maximizing his S rank potential, exploiting critical hits, and leveraging multi-hit combos for extreme burst damage. Strengths: Insane single-target and AoE burst, rapid perfection scaling, extreme critical hit potential, highly versatile with multiple viable builds.\n\nSteeled Strike \u2013 Thirteen-hit skill for maximum multi-hit scaling, perfect for stacking perfection rapidly. Contorso \u2013 Lightning strike on critical hits, triggers additional hits for massive multi-hit scaling. At Rank S, this weapon guarantees critical hits, making it perfect for rapid perfection stacking. Lanceram \u2013 Stability weapon that prevents rank drops below C, ideal for players struggling to maintain high ranks. Its high base attack also makes it a solid mid-game option for steady damage output. Danseso \u2013 High critical scaling and agility bonuses, excellent for rapid rank gains and burst damage. At Level 20, it grants 1 Perfection per Burn on the target, making it effective in burn-heavy builds. Cheater \u2013 Allows for consecutive turns, crucial for maximizing DPS in extended encounters. Critical Burn \u2013 Increases critical chance against burning targets, pairs well with light damage builds.",
