        "text": "When Verso uses Frenzy and Double Third, they greatly increase the damage of his Steeled Strike skill. The weapons and Luminas absolutely take his strike to the next level and allow Verso to delete enemies during combat.\n\nHere are the best teams that players can bring to battle in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, complete with information for their builds and strategies.\n\nGrinding out levels is a part of every RPG, and Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 is no different. Here is how players can level up the quickest. ... On the other hand, since this team won\u2019t have a dedicated sustain character, nor someone who applies Shell for the team, it\u2019s good to build Maelle with Guard Up to increase her team\u2019s sustainability. Considering Verso is responsible for applying Burn while Maelle will deal high damage because of it, Lune\u2019s job is to break enemies and double the amount of Burn on them. This will skyrocket the amount of Burn on enemies and the damage it deals. With her Earth skills, Lune is more than capable of handling this role while making sure everyone in the team is healed and protected. In this team comp, instead of Verso dealing damage with his Base Attack and Burning damage, he'll fully focus on his Steeled Strike, which charges for two turns.\n\nWhen Verso uses Frenzy and Double Third, they greatly increase the damage of his Steeled Strike skill. The weapons and Luminas absolutely take his strike to the next level and allow Verso to delete enemies during combat. In a perfect rotation, Verso should get his turn with 9 AP on the S Rank. Players can then cast Steeled Strike and charge it to the next turn, which is immediately after because of the Cheater Lumina. In case Verso's turn started and he didn't have 9 AP or the S Rank, players can cast Overload, and that skill will refill Verso's AP and increase his Rank. Since Cheater is already a core Lumina for Verso, players can include a couple of other Luminas that take advantage of Verso getting back his turn. Clea's Life, for instance, nullifies the price Verso pays when using the Overload skill. The most important skill for Monoco in this team is the Boucheclier Fortify, as it will heavily buff their allies and fill their AP.\n\nWhile Verso barely has any skills that synergize with the Burn status, he\u2019s one of the best characters that apply Burn in Clair Obscur Expedition 33. Add Maelle and Lune, who both have a core gameplay with Fire and Burn, and players will build a strong Burn team in Expedition 33. This team focuses on single-target damage and can be slow during combat, but it prioritizes safety while enemies are slowly falling to Burn damage. Building Verso with Corpeso grants him the ability to install an enormous amount of Burn status on enemies using his Base Attack. Players can build an arsenal of Luminas that buff Verso\u2019s Base Attack, maximizing the utility of these hits. As for Verso\u2019s skills, it\u2019s better to have some sustain skills since players won\u2019t use them as long as Verso is healthy and kicking. Since Verso is the one who\u2019s installing Burn, Maelle could be the one who takes advantage of it.",
