        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Open with Focused Foretell (or Searing Bond if the target is burning). Stack further with Spectral Sweep on durable targets. Stacking Foretell and using these powerful skills can help stunlock bosses, allowing your team to control tough encounters ...\n\nSupport Sciel supercharges high-damage allies. Fortune\u2019s Fury + Intervention turns Verso Follow Up/Phantom Stars/End Bringer and Free Aim shots into tactical nukes on demand. Lune Wildfire sets up Searing Bond; Sciel then doubles Lune\u2019s burst and feeds her more AP for Lightning Dance/Genesis. Lastly Maelle, who is already capable of one-shotting everything in the game solo or as main dps, doubling her damage on top of her ridiculous kit ends encounters instantly and trivializes the game. Team synergies are also vital. Pair Sciel with allies who can apply status effects like Bad Omen, which increases the damage enemies take. Skills like Fortune\u2019s Fury can grant Sciel an immediate turn, letting her apply or consume Foretell stacks at the perfect moment for maximum impact. Check out the best builds for Clair Obscure: Expedition 33 linked below!\n\nLitheson is the endgame support weapon of choice, it scales with Agility + Luck which is great. It grants allies Greater Rush and debuffs enemies with Greater Slow. Allowing your team to have a major speed advantage. Additionally this weapon helps her greatly with AP generation allowing you to spam your two core abilities without ever running dry. For maximizing Sciel\u2019s damage output, Charnon is Sciel\u2019s default weapon and is considered the optimal late-game choice. Charnon\u2019s passive effects guarantee critical hits during Twilight State, resulting in increased damage and excellent synergy with Sciel\u2019s abilities. The following Lumina and Pictos are recommended for the Support Sciel Build in Clair Obscure: Expedition 33. Sciel\u2019s early game Lumina and Pictos focus on counter-heavy openings, rapid turn acceleration, and layered burn and crit bonuses, backed by strong early pressure, high-risk burst options, and a touch of late-fight stability to keep her momentum going in tougher battles.\n\nOpen with Focused Foretell (or Searing Bond if the target is burning). Stack further with Spectral Sweep on durable targets. Stacking Foretell and using these powerful skills can help stunlock bosses, allowing your team to control tough encounters and prevent dangerous attacks. Bank AP for your teammates via Plentiful Harvest when stacks are high; Intervention your carry to hand them your turn for more damage. Lastly, if cleanup is needed, Sealed Fate cashes Foretell into lethal damage. The Lune synergy is the real power early on Wildfire into Searing Bond gives large AoE damage and foretell application that can carry Acts 1\u20132 by itself. Act 3 is where Sciel becomes a pure pocket support and the party\u2019s force multiplier. Replace Focused Foretell with Fortune\u2019s Fury, which will target an ally to double their damage for one turn. This scales harder and harder as numbers uncap, making it far more valuable late (turning 3M into 6M matters more than turning 9,999 into 19,998 did).\n\nMaster this Expedition 33 Sciel build including essential skills, weapons, and strategies to enhance your gameplay. This guide also covers the best pictos for maximizing Sciel\u2019s performance as a powerful support build, so read on! This build is up to date for Clair Obscure: Expedition 33 Update 1.5.0! ... Learn how to use the ultimate support character in Expedition 33 with the Support Sciel Build! Our guide on Sciel will show you the best recommendations for weapons, luminas, skills and combos. Having Sciel as the only active party member can enhance combat effectiveness by allowing you to focus on her health and maximize her critical hit potential. Effects like foretell consumed become even more valuable during tightly scripted encounters. We hope you enjoy this build on your journey to defeat the Paintress. Support Sciel is the perfect engine for your team, providing them with extra turns, more AP and extra damage.",
