        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Finally and this is my personal favorite as it makes a mockery out of bosses and makes the super bosses much easier to deal with, Delaying Slash. You can get this skill super early compared to the others and it can seriously carry the party. It is a moon skill which consumes Foretell to increase ...\n\nAnother skill Intervention for a mere 5 AP she can grant an ally 4 AP and then have them play immediately, thus allowing you to more easily control turn order. Another skill Fortune's Fury allows an ally to deal double damage for 1 turn. Finally and this is my personal favorite as it makes a mockery out of bosses and makes the super bosses much easier to deal with, Delaying Slash. You can get this skill super early compared to the others and it can seriously carry the party. It is a moon skill which consumes Foretell to increase damage AND DELAY THE TARGET'S NEXT TURN. While the delaying effect is still subject to the enemy's base speed (a very fast boss may not be as effected such certain super bosses on NG+). It does hinge on how much Foretell you place on the target before hand and hence consume. Her other skills make her a decent damage dealer with the right set up but for me personally speaking she is best as a Turn controlling support member.\n\nSciel is the mood maker of the party and that remains true in battle as her skills allow her to play many different roles as a true jack of all trades. Sciel's gimmick is perhaps the most immediately confusing when players immediately start out, this is both due to the confusing tutorials and the growing number of symbols and gimmicks in the game during her introduction. Sciel's skills can do 2 things, place Foretell on the enemy and grant herself Sun or Moon Charges. Foretell are essentially an ailment as the cards she throws at enemies lodge themselves in their bodies. Initially only a maximum of 10 Foretell can be active on a single enemy. Skills that place foretell on enemies typically grant her a Sun Charge, you can think of these like Maelle's stances which grant her an additional effect when active, more on that later. Her other type of skill can then Consume the Foretells placed on enemies to deal greater damage or cause other effects, these skills will grant a moon charge.\n\nSciel is a hard character to get a grasp on in more ways than one but when you do she is easily a main stay on the party. Weapon wise it really comes down to how you want to use her, each of her weapons have passive which add effects to her various charges or changes something about how Foretell is applied. It's a bit trickier to lock down her best weapons.",
