        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "For Sciel, use the Charnon weapon while focusing on the Luck and Defense attributes. This increases her survivability while also increasing her other stats thanks to the weapon&#x27;s scaling.\n\n\u2605 Builds: Gustave | Lune | Maelle \u2517 Sciel | Verso | Monoco \u2605 Popular: Missables | Puzzles | White Nevrons \u2517 Best Characters | Skills | Teams | Attributes \u2605 Patch 1.5.0: Verso's Drafts | Root of All Evil \u2517 Endless Tower Guide | All New Bosses \u00b7 Here are the best character builds in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. See early, mid, and late game builds here! ... For Gustave, use the Abysseram weapon while focusing on the Vitality and Agility attributes. This increases his Health and Speed, allowing him to take a lot of turns and be more tanky at the same time. The Pictos and Luminas let him inflict debuffs on the enemies. ... For Maelle, use the Medalum weapon while focusing on the Defense and Agility attributes. This increases her Speed and Defense while raising her Attack and Crit thanks to the attribute scaling. The Pictos and Luminas give more offensive stats and strengthen her parries, including a big damage boost for not getting hit.\n\nFor Sciel, use the Charnon weapon while focusing on the Luck and Defense attributes. This increases her survivability while also increasing her other stats thanks to the weapon's scaling. The Pictos and Luminas give her a lot of offensive stats, damage boosts, and AP recovery. ... For Verso, use the Chevalam weapon while focusing on the Agility and Luck attributes. This increases his Speed and Crit chance while also allowing him to start at S Rank immediately. The Pictos and Luminas give him a lot of damage boosts and strengthen his parries in exchange for being unable to be healed. ... For Monoco, use the Joyaro weapon while focusing on the Agility and Defense attributes. Not only does this increase his Speed, but it also increases your other stats thanks to Joyaro's scaling. The Pictos and Luminas give him increased damage, more power to his parries, and increased potential for Breaking.\n\nBuilds in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 is influenced by the character's attributes. These attributes contribute greatly to how a character performs or plays and are the deciding factor in whether the build works or not. Make sure to level up your attributes according to the build you're going for. This is mostly decided by the weapon the character is using. ... Weapons have attribute scaling and can increase a character's stats depending on what attribute scaling it has. Prioritize leveling up the attribute the weapon scales with since it'll give you additional stats which is beneficial in the long run. ... Pictos and Lumina are also a major part of a character's build since they can provide effects that can boost specific attacks and skills, and even offer buffs. Match Pictos and Lumina that synergize with each other to enhance the build you're planning on using.",
