          "site_name": "Game-Rezone"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Final Path \u2013 hard-hitting single-target move with Break potential. Intervention \u2013 lets an ally act immediately and grants them 4 AP. Fortune\u2019s Fury \u2013 doubles an ally\u2019s damage for one turn and applies Twilight.\n\nLate Game: Rotate Fortune\u2019s Fury \u2192 Focused Foretell \u2192 Twilight Dance/Final Path for huge spike turns. Use Intervention to accelerate an ally\u2019s turn and keep momentum high. Team Role: Sciel works best as a tempo-setter, controlling the pace of battle with Foretell setups, Twilight bursts, and AP support for the party. Sciel is more than just a Foretell damage dealer \u2014 she evolves into the engine of your squad. With the right build, she delivers reliable burst damage through Twilight while also keeping allies empowered with AP and buffs. Whether you lean on her for offense or utility, Sciel will remain one of the most impactful characters in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33.\n\nFocused Foretell \u2013 continues to drive Sciel\u2019s setup. Marking Card \u2013 reliable Foretell generator. Twilight Slash \u2013 quick Foretell consumer. Sealed Fate \u2013 core burst damage option. Grim Harvest \u2013 deals damage and heals allies, stronger with Foretell. Plentiful Harvest \u2013 consumes Foretell to grant AP to an ally. Twilight Dance \u2013 multi-hit finisher that extends Twilight. Sealed Fate \u2013 remains a powerful Foretell-based nuke. Final Path \u2013 hard-hitting single-target move with Break potential. Intervention \u2013 lets an ally act immediately and grants them 4 AP. Fortune\u2019s Fury \u2013 doubles an ally\u2019s damage for one turn and applies Twilight. Plentiful Harvest \u2013 AP generation to keep the team rolling. Immaculate \u2013 increases damage by 30% until Sciel takes a hit. Glass Canon \u2013 huge offensive boost at the cost of defense. Inverted Affinity \u2013 extra damage when exploiting status alignment.\n\nSciel is one of the most versatile characters in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. She starts out as a high-damage dealer focused on the Foretell mechanic, but as the game progresses, she evolves into a hybrid role \u2014 providing AP, buffs, and even healing while still dishing out huge Twilight damage. This guide covers the best attributes, weapons, skills, Pictos, and Luminas for each act. Agility \u2013 primary for turn order and action tempo. Luck \u2013 boosts crit rate and consistency. Vitality \u2013 a small investment for survivability. Agility \u2013 keep pushing for faster cycles. Defense \u2013 pairs well with mid-game weapon scaling. Optional: a few points in Vitality for comfort. Defense \u2013 primary scaling and sturdiness late-game. Luck \u2013 crit synergy for burst windows. Optional: minor Agility if you need tighter turn control. Excellent early-game option with strong scaling in Agility and Luck.\n\nBalanced weapon that synergizes with Agility and Defense. Its passive effect reduces healing costs, giving Sciel more sustain in longer fights. Top-tier choice for late game. Guarantees critical hits during Twilight, unlocking Sciel\u2019s maximum DPS potential and pairing perfectly with her Foretell mechanics. A situational option that applies Marks and transfers Foretell after an enemy\u2019s death. Useful in hybrid support builds but outclassed by Charnon in raw damage. Sciel can equip up to six skills at a time. Here are the best loadouts for each act: Focused Foretell \u2013 applies Foretell and builds the core mechanic. Marking Card \u2013 places Marks and stacks Foretell quickly. Spectral Sweep \u2013 multi-hit move, each strike adds Foretell. Twilight Slash \u2013 consumes Foretell for extra damage. Phantom Blade \u2013 strong single-target attack, can trigger Break.",
        "is_citable": true,
        "prompt_context_metadata": {
          "url": "https://game-rezone.com/en/guide/clair-obscur-expedition-33-best-sciel-build/",
          "search_provider": "anthropic",
          "age": "September 9, 2025"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "knowledge",
        "title": "Best Attributes and Skills for Sciel in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33",
        "url": "https://gamerant.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-best-sciel-build-e33-attributes-skills/",
        "metadata": {
          "type": "webpage_metadata",
          "site_domain": "gamerant.com",
          "favicon_url": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=gamerant.com",
          "site_name": "Game Rant"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Start by using Card Weaver, then follow up with a Moon skill to enter Twilight mode on Sciel&#x27;s first turn. In general, start by casting Card Weaver, then follow up with Phantom Blade or Dark Wave (whichever fits the situation more).\n\nWhen it comes to boss fights or fights against other tough targets, you'll be able to keep your Foretell stacks maxed out, thus making sure that Sciel is always doing the most damage she possibly can. Don't forget to use Rush to increase the team's speed and Fortune's Fury to give someone in the team a double damage buff.\n\nMuch like the other Expeditioners, Sciel in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 is capable of both tremendous utility and amazing damage. She uses her unique Sun & Moon mechanic to supercharge her abilities, allowing her to deal with every enemy in the Expedition's way with relative ease. Sciel's kit is a little confusing at first, but once you become familiar with what she can do, you'll realize exactly how strong she can be in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. This build guide aims to make Sciel a DPS powerhouse who can consistently reach (and blow past) the damage cap starting in Act 2. ... Yellow Harvest is a sub-region in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 with a lot of loot for you to collect. Here's a guide to all collectibles in the area. ... This good thing about this build is players can start using the very basic form of it as soon as they get Chation, a weapon that makes all of Sciel's Sun Skills apply 10 Foretell on enemies.\n\nThis build is all about striking first and striking hard. If you start your turn with a different party member, consider giving Sciel an Energy Tint so she can start with Dark Wave instead of Phantom Blade. Your choice of Luminas here will vary depending on your preferences and playstyle. For starters, try the following: ... Breaker and Breaking Counter are mostly for breaking enemies with Counterattacks (also with Phantom Blade), while the rest are for improving Sciel's AP economy. Alternatively, you can try getting the Last Stand Pictos from the Hidden Gestral Arena to turn Sciel into a powerful solo fighter. You can use Inverted Affinity as a Lumina and equip the Confident Picto instead. The latter dampens Chation's drawback by making Sciel take 50% less damage. However, this will completely prevent her from getting healed. If your battles are lasting for more than three turns, consider replacing Inverted Affinity with something else, like Shield Affinity.\n\nSciel doesn't really need a team to function well with this build, but she'll appreciate anyone who can apply buffs and debuffs. Maelle is especially helpful since she can apply Defenceless with Offensive Switch, but anyone can do the same with the right Pictos equipped. As mentioned, this build gives Sciel a headstart on Foretell application via Card Weaver and Chation's passive effect. Starting with 10 Foretell on every enemy is a huge advantage, and if you have Painted Power and enough AP to kick things off with Dark Wave, fights will be over before they even begin. In practice, it's much like the Auto Death build but with more steps. Start by using Card Weaver, then follow up with a Moon skill to enter Twilight mode on Sciel's first turn. In general, start by casting Card Weaver, then follow up with Phantom Blade or Dark Wave (whichever fits the situation more).",
        "is_citable": true,
        "prompt_context_metadata": {
          "url": "https://gamerant.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-best-sciel-build-e33-attributes-skills/",
