          "age": "May 8, 2025"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "knowledge",
        "title": "Endgame Burn Stacking Build (Expert and NG+) - Clair Obscur Expedition 33",
        "url": "https://maxroll.gg/clair-obscur-expedition-33/guides/endgame-burn-stacking-build-expert-and-ng",
        "metadata": {
          "type": "webpage_metadata",
          "site_domain": "maxroll.gg",
          "favicon_url": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=maxroll.gg",
          "site_name": "Maxroll.gg"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "On Sciel&#x27;s second turn, use Intervention on an ally who plays after the enemies to advance their turn. You can fill her remaining skill slots with damage/utility effects based on personal preference.\n\nUse Fortune's Fury on Maelle to double her damage. Occasionally, you might use this on Verso instead (such as if Maelle has the buff active already). On Sciel's second turn, use Intervention on an ally who plays after the enemies to advance their turn. You can fill her remaining skill slots with damage/utility effects based on personal preference. Sometimes you want to use Fortune's Fury into another Sun skill, such as Marking Card to debuff enemies or a second cast of Fortune's Fury. Use double Sun skills when allies already go before the enemies. Run Energy Master to save the Lumina points, but aside from this, her Pictos are not important; prioritize Pictos with a high Speed stat. ... For your remaining Lumina points, you can add extra utility, defenses, or damage. In Medias Res should cover most of your defenses, but additional shield synergies and revival effects are nice if enemies get a turn and you mess up.\n\nFor single tanky enemies like bosses - Verso > Sciel > Maelle. This way Verso can stack burns on the target, then Sciel can buff Maelle with double damage and give Verso a second turn. Then, Maelle can nuke the enemy. If you don't have the damage to kill them before they get a turn because you're missing levels/weapon levels or Luminas, use the \"group\" setup below instead. For groups of 2-3 dangerous foes - Verso > Maelle > Sciel. With this setup, Verso still stacks burns, but now splits them between multiple targets. Maelle nukes the first boss, then re-enters Virtuose stance. After that, Sciel gives her double damage and a second turn to deal with the next boss. The easiest way to swap the party order when following this guide is by swapping Survivor out on Sciel for Auto Death as this clears the Rush from Auto Rush. ... Verso's job is stacking burn effects on enemies.\n\nVerso's most important Luminas are all related to inflicting burn and getting AP back to inflict more burn stacks on enemies. This is the \"burn stack\" portion of the build that gives it its namesake. The additional Luminas enable his ability to deal damage. Thanks to Sniper your first Free Aim Shot can break enemies, remember this and don't waste it. You can't nuke a boss out of nowhere with this setup, the way Maelle can, but between the repeated damage from Free Aim Shot and Attack, you can significantly lower an enemy's health and then finish them off with the burn tick when their turn starts. Longer Burn is not used because enemies do not survive long enough for this to matter. Adding Charging Stun in for when Sciel primes enemies to be stunned means you can full charge a level 3 Gradient for Maelle. ... Maelle is your damage carry, deleting enemies with a single use of Burning Canvas.\n\nFire damage or even absorb it! Since she is built for damage, your first 3 turns are the strongest, and you can use Sciel to double her damage for 1 turn. Your first weapon, Medalum starts you in Virtuose stance, allowing for incredible damage in the opening round. This weapon also doubles the burn stacks Maelle inflicts and doubles the damage from her burn effects. But most of the time, Burning Canvas kills enemies instantly, rendering this moot. You obtain this weapon by playing as Maelle in the Gestral Arena. Attributes: Def > Agi > Might (the Def is just for damage scaling) While starting in Virtuose stance is nice, you don't need a specific weapon; if you use something else, adjust your Attributes to match your weapon's primary scaling. ... Brulerum (burn on crit), or Lithum (maintain Mark on enemies for slightly more damage). Use Yeverum to stack shields on allies for more defense, but you should have plenty of shields/revive effects regardless of this.",
