        "text": "Fortune&#x27;s Fury, Rush, and Harvest are great picks, where Fortune&#x27;s Fury can increase damage to allies, Rush grants additional turns, and Harvest can heal her while also dealing damage.\n\nLastly, you'll want to have a couple of buff skills equipped for Sciel. Fortune's Fury, Rush, and Harvest are great picks, where Fortune's Fury can increase damage to allies, Rush grants additional turns, and Harvest can heal her while also dealing damage. As you reach level 30 to 50 and make it to the \"endgame\" of Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, you'll get access to even better skills for Sciel. Her purpose remains the same though, which is to gather AP and build Foretell to maximize her damage output. Out of all the late game skills for Sciel, the grid below shows the best options. As you can see, we're keeping Fortune's Fury into the endgame, mainly because it's a great way to buff allies for Gradient Attacks. ... Time travel is a finicky theme to get right, but when a JRPG nails it, the results are marvelous. ... As for the new skills added, Final Path is the standout here due to the Extreme Dark damage it deals.\n\nSciel is the fourth member to join the party in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. She has a unique mechanic where she builds up \"Foretell\" through skills for extra damage. Depending on how you build Sciel, she can turn into one of the strongest party members in the game. ... Never judge a book by its cover or a JRPG by its excessively anime protagonist. ... However, focusing on the wrong skills and Pictos can also result in her being pretty weak. That's where this build guide comes in. Read further to learn how to create the best Sciel build in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. Creating a strong Sciel build in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 boils down to unlocking her strongest skills, equipping the best Pictos, and selecting a weapon that grants the best buffs and attack power. Sciel is a character that deals Dark and Physical damage through her skills. As Sciel uses skills, she applies Foretell to enemies (10 max per enemy) that generate Sun charges.\n\nDepending on where you're currently at in your playthrough of Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, the best skills for Sciel change. For this reason, below you will find the best skills for the early game and the endgame. Once you first unlock Sciel as a party member in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, she has two skills available: Twilight Slash and Focused Foretell. As you level her up, there are a handful of skills you should aim to unlock to create the best build and help defeat early game bosses. To start off, we have Searing Bond. This useful early game skill does a decent amount of damage, but that's not what makes it so useful. The major benefit here is that it applies a guaranteed 5 Foretell and also does the same to each burning enemy on the battlefield. This gives Sciel a major advantage and shoots her closer to the max 10 Foretell. Spectral Sweep is a good addition as it's a consecutive attack skill (2 to 6 hits), where each hit applies Foretell.\n\nWhile the Attack Power of a weapon is important in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, it's not the only aspect that can make a difference. Most weapons come equipped with three buffs that are unlocked once the player upgrades them to a certain level. When it comes to the best weapon for Sciel, you want to make sure to have a decent Attack Power, but most importantly, you want weapons that come equipped with strong effects. Early on in your playthrough, the best weapon to choose is the Rangeson. This strong early-game weapon has good attack power (increases when upgraded), deals Dark Damage, and scales with Defense (C) and Agility (B). Even better, the Rangeson comes with three buffs that can be unlocked at specific levels: Level 4: Recover 5% Health per Foretell applied. Level 10: Healing Skills cost 1 less AP. Level 20: 30% increased Heal efficiency per Moon charge. Base Attack gives 1 Moon Charge. The best endgame weapon to finish off this Sciel build is the Chation, with a base attack pow",
