    "thinking": "Good. I have enough info to give a solid answer now. Let me synthesize what I've found for the endgame team of Maelle + Sciel + Verso, with the playstyle constraints in mind.\n\n**Maelle (Primary DPS)**\nEndgame skills: She's using Lithum in endgame. The core skills are:\n- Stendhal - core nuke, devastating in Virtuose Stance\n- Sword Ballet - crit-heavy burst\n- Burning Canvas / Pyrolyse - fire damage\n- Gustave's Homage - her gradient skill effectively\n- Swift Stride / Last Chance - to re-enter Virtuose stance\n\n\n- Fleuret Fury - multi-hit for breaking\n\nLooking at her full skill pool, I can see she has access to quite a range of options beyond the basics. The question is which ones synergize best with Lithum and the Virtuose Stance playstyle I'm building around. Some of the utility skills like Payback and Guard Down might have niche uses, but the damage-focused ones seem more aligned with what I need for endgame content.\n\nThe core issue is that Lithum shifts her damage profile toward Void rather than pure burn scaling, which means Burning Canvas might actually be stronger than I initially thought despite the weapon change. I should verify whether the Maxroll recommendation for Burning Canvas as the primary nuke still holds up with Lithum, or if I need to pivot toward Stendhal as the main burst tool instead. With Lithum, Burning Canvas and Pyrolyse still work effectively since they're fire skills and Lithum doesn't strip the marks that Gustave's Homage relies on. For Maelle's endgame rotation, the consensus from the sources points to Stendhal as the core Virtuose nuke, Burning Canvas for fire damage, Sword Ballet or Perc\u00e9e as backup, Fleuret Fury for breaking, Swift Stride or Last Chance to re-enter stance, and either Payback or Gustave's Homage to round it out. Now looking at Verso's endgame DPS build, the standard Chevalam/Gaulteram approach focuses on Quick Strike for rank jumping, Assault Zero for AP recovery and rank gains, and Steeled Strike as additional damage. hit, his main damage skill with Cheater)\n- End Bringer (6 hits, bonus vs stunned, rank A effect)\n- Phantom Stars (AoE at S rank) - but this only matters for multi-enemy, boss fights it's useless\n- Marking Shot or Defiant Strike (for applying Mark)\n\nWait, from the Game8 source: \"Quick Strike to jump to Rank B. Afterward, use Assault Zero until you reach Rank A. Lastly, use Light Holder to recover AP and jump to Rank S... then Defiant Strike for damage + Mark.\" \n\nBut the overview says Verso does NOT have Light Holder and End Bringer. However the user asked \"assuming I can unlock any skills\" - so this is the aspirational/endgame answer.\n\nFor Verso's endgame with Chevalam (starts at S rank, so no rank-climbing needed), the rank-climbing skills matter less since he can immediately start dealing damage. With Matt's playstyle constraints avoiding Defiant Strike while parry is developing, I'd prioritize Quick Strike for Perfection gain, Assault Zero for AP generation and rank maintenance, and Steeled Strike as the primary damage dealer, then round out with either Marking Shot or a utility skill depending on the situation.\n\nFor Sciel's support role, Fortune's Fury and Intervention are the essential core skills\u2014Fortune's Fury doubles ally damage while Intervention gives an ally 4 AP and an immediate turn, both critical for enabling burst damage. The Maxroll source emphasizes these two as the foundation of the burn stacking team.\n\nDelaying Slash stands out as a powerful but underrated option for boss control since it directly delays enemy turns, giving the team more breathing room. I should also note some practical constraints: Verso doesn't currently have Steeled Strike, End Bringer, or Light Holder (though Light Holder becomes less necessary once Chevalam is equipped and you start at S rank), and Matt's conservative approach to parry means high-risk skills like Defiant Strike with its 30% HP cost aren't ideal for him yet.\n\nFor Maelle, I'm checking which skills she actually has versus which ones might be unlockable\u2014she's got Gustave's Homage, Sword Ballet, Fleuret Fury, Perc\u00e9e, Fencer's Flurry, Swift Stride, and Stendhal confirmed, but skills like Burning Canvas, Pyrolyse, Last Chance, and Payback appear to be unlockable options I can include given the user's assumption about accessing any skill.\n\nNow I'm cross-referencing all the confirmed abilities across the three characters to make sure I'm not mixing anything up, and I have a solid list for each of them ready to build the answer.",
