    "text": "Good enough across all three. Here's my synthesis, filtered through your playstyle constraints.\n\n---\n\n**Maelle** (endgame DPS with Lithum)\n\nThe core loop is getting into and staying in Virtuose Stance, then nuking. Stendhal and Sword Ballet are her primary single-target damage tools in Virtuose, and Burning Canvas is a devastating fire nuke. Gustave's Homage benefits from marked targets, and Lithum's passive maintains marks rather than consuming them, making the two synergise well.\n\nRecommended 6:\n1. **Stendhal** \u2014 primary Virtuose nuke\n2. **Burning Canvas** \u2014 fire burst (extremely powerful, confirmed as a key endgame skill)\n3. **Sword Ballet** \u2014 crit-heavy backup burst\n4. **Fleuret Fury** \u2014 breaking + multi-hit\n5. **Last Chance** \u2014 re-enters Virtuose Stance when lost\n6. **Payback** \u2014 high-damage counter after parries, good AP synergy\n\nSwift Stride is a viable alternative to Last Chance if you prefer proactive stance entry. I'm less certain about the relative priority of Payback vs Gustave's Homage in slot 6 \u2014 both appear in endgame builds, and the choice may depend on how reliably you're landing parries.\n\n---\n\n**Verso** (endgame DPS with Chevalam)\n\nWith Chevalam in Act 3, you start at S Rank immediately, so you don't need to burn turns climbing to it \u2014 you can deal damage from turn one. That makes the rank-climbing skills (Quick Strike, Assault Zero) less critical, though still useful for Perfection maintenance after hits.\n\nEnd Bringer is described as Verso's strongest skill \u2014 extreme damage for 6 hits, with bonus damage and extended stun at Rank A. Steeled Strike hits 13 times, making it excellent for multi-hit scaling when paired with Cheater.\n\nRecommended 6 (playstyle-filtered \u2014 no Defiant Strike):\n1. **Steeled Strike** \u2014 13-hit primary damage skill\n2. **End Bringer** \u2014 6-hit nuke, bonus vs stunned enemies\n3. **Quick Strike** \u2014 Perfection gain + fallback rank tool\n4. **Assault Zero** \u2014 AP recovery + rank maintenance\n5. **Marking Shot** \u2014 applies Mark safely, no HP cost\n6. **Perfect Break** \u2014 single-target breaking + high damage\n\nPhantom Stars could replace Perfect Break if you're fighting groups, but it's useless in 1v1. For boss fights, Perfect Break is cleaner.\n\nNote: Verso currently doesn't have Steeled Strike or End Bringer \u2014 both require progression (Steeled Strike needs Cheater Pictos from Sprong first).\n\n---\n\n**Sciel** (pure support)\n\nFortune's Fury, Intervention, and Delaying Slash are cited as making Sciel by far the best support in the game \u2014 every top endgame setup starts with Sciel.\n\nIn Act 3, Fortune's Fury becomes her most impactful tool \u2014 doubling damage scales harder as numbers grow uncapped, and Intervention lets an ally act immediately with 4 AP, controlling turn order precisely.\n\nRecommended 6:\n1. **Fortune's Fury** \u2014 double an ally's damage (Maelle primary target)\n2. **Intervention** \u2014 give ally an immediate turn + 4 AP\n3. **Delaying Slash** \u2014 delays enemy's next turn (powerful boss control, confirmed as a standout skill)\n4. **Plentiful Harvest** \u2014 AP generation to ally based on Foretell stacks\n5. **Focused Foretell** \u2014 Foretell generation (enables Plentiful Harvest + Delaying Slash)\n6. **Final Path** \u2014 her hardest-hitting damage skill when you have a free slot\n\nThe 5th and 6th slots are more flexible than 1\u20134. Sealed Fate or Twilight Dance could replace Final Path if you want more damage or Twilight extension respectively. Grim Harvest is an option if you need party healing, though your current Sciel build doesn't prioritise that role.\n\n---\n\n**One caveat:** I'm reasonably confident about the core skills (Fortune's Fury, Intervention, Steeled Strike, End Bringer, Burning Canvas, Stendhal) based on multiple sources. I'm less certain about exact slot priorities in the flex positions, and I haven't simulated actual turn sequences here \u2014 this is build-level reasoning rather than combat simulation. If anything looks off once you're testing it in practice, flag it.",
