 to dive into their next game.\n\nFind the best tips, guides, and strategies for Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 below: Ultimate Verso Build Guide (Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies) Lune Build Guide \u2013 Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies \u00b7 Ultimate Gustave Build Guide (Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies) Ultimate Sciel Build Guide (Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies) Maelle Build Guide \u2013 Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies ... Unmatched Flexibility: Monoco is like the Swiss Army knife of characters. He can fill almost any role depending on your team composition, and he does it with style. He\u2019s basically the guy who says, \u201cI got this\u201d while your team looks at their weapons like they\u2019re still figuring out how to equip them. High Break Potential: Monoco has more break abilities than a wrecking ball at demolition day. This makes him invaluable in controlling tough fights and breaking enemy defenses\u2014no more \u201cspaghetti arms\u201d bosses.\n\nVerso (DPS): Provides extreme burst damage and finishing power. When Monoco is softening up the enemy, Verso finishes the job. Fighting bosses in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 is no joke. You need precise timing and strategy. Monoco, when played correctly, can make these fights look easy. Here\u2019s how to make sure you\u2019re not the one getting squashed under the boss\u2019s boot: Break and Burst: Use skills like Duallist Storm and Chapelier Slash to quickly apply marks and break shields, setting up for some serious burst damage. Because breaking shields isn\u2019t enough\u2014now it\u2019s time to break the enemy\u2019s spirit. Stack Shields Before Bursts: Use Cruler Barrier to build up shields and maximize damage with Powerful Shield before going for the big hits. After all, you need some defense before you turn the tables and unleash hell. Exploit Elemental Weaknesses: Rotate through abilities like Glaise Earthquakes and Cr\u00e9ation Void to exploit elemental weaknesses.",
