        "text": "Luminas like Energising Shell, Energising Powerful, Energising Turn, and Energy Master are amazing for building up Monoco\u2019s AP every time he casts an upgraded Skill, especially Boucheclier Fortify.\n\nWhether it's as a support or DPS, Monoco can do it all in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33.\n\nMonoco is one of the most unique Gestrals in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. Players will meet him at Monoco's Station, and soon learn that he has the ability to turn into a Nevron. Monoco does this by collecting Nevron feet, although the exact process is unknown. Thanks to his love of collecting Nevron feet, Monoco has a large variety of skills to choose from. This allows him to do so much during combat, including healing, buffing, debuffing, dealing damage, or all of these together. If players are overwhelmed by how much Monoco can do, then this guide can help by narrowing the viable setups for Monoco build in Expedition 33. Updated on December 15, 2025, by Nahda Nabiilah: Monoco may not look like a typical Gestral in the Expedition 33 canvas, but rest assured, he is. The Gestrals were designed based on the childhood idea of a pet dog, signified by Monoco's name, which is based on the family's dog.\n\nDue to his origin, it's no surprise Monoco has a thing for feet, resembling a dog's love for bones. Monoco's ability to steal skills from other Nevrons makes him a unique playable character in E33 who can excel in different roles and situations. Monoco can be an amazing support in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. Many characters can rival Monoco on DPS, but none can rival his amazing range of supportive abilities. Within his kit, Monoco can heal, shield, and buff the team or debuff enemies. Essential Luminas when using Monoco's Base Attack: Essential Luminas when casting Boucheclier Fortify: To benefit from Monoco\u2019s supportive role, build Monoco with the Ballaroweapon to create a continuous AP generator. He can generate AP from multiple sources, but it\u2019s always good to have a passive energy source. Ballaroreverses the Bestial Wheel, and that helps the Wheel Pointer land more often on the Heavy and Caster Masks, which have the most supportive skills out of the other Masks.\n\nLuminas like Energising Shell, Energising Powerful, Energising Turn, and Energy Master are amazing for building up Monoco\u2019s AP every time he casts an upgraded Skill, especially Boucheclier Fortify. Not to mention, Sidarohelps Monoco gain some AP when casting an upgraded skill, further proving itself as one of the best weapons for DPS Monoco in Expedition 33. Most of Monoco\u2019s attacks are AoE in this build, with Creation Void attacking random targets and being devastating against bosses. The idea behind this Monoco\u2019s build is to set the field ready by the team and completely buff Monoco to deal some of the highest damage in the game. ... While there are plenty of Lumina points to go around, some characters should be prioritized in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. ... Monoco's attacks in this DPS build are designed to keep spinning the wheel in the same direction.",
