        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Combo Attack and Cheater can help Monoco stay ahead of his AP needs, but it&#x27;s a good idea to add to his overall gain with Energising Turn.Time Tint, and Energising Stun. The latter is especially useful for Monoco, since he&#x27;s going to be Stunning ...\n\nShatter and stun your foes as Expedition 33's Gestral companion!\n\nMonoco has more Skills available than any other character in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, so it can be tricky to figure out exactly how best to set him up for success. He can do it all, but not all at once, so eventually you'll have to choose what role in the party you'll want him to fill. ... Turn the Nevrons' powers against them with Monoco, the final member of Expedition 33. ... As it turns out, there's no better character in the game for quickly filling enemy Break Meters and stunning them, shattering their defenses and leaving them wide open for attack. Here's how to make Monoco a certifiable barrier-breaker. Monoco has a couple of weapons that enhance his Break capabilities; the two main candidates are the Lightning-elemental Joyaro and Earth-elemental Urnaro. Of the two, Joyaro is the more effective, as it's focused more on helping you Break enemies, while Urnaro is more about rewarding you when you do so.\n\nJust filling an enemy's Break Meter isn't enough to shatter their defenses in Clair Obscur. ... With Joyaro equipped, Monoco is guaranteed to get double Break Damage on the first Skill he uses, as well as its Mask bonus, since he's going to be in Almighty at the start of every fight. That means you should open with the biggest, hardest-hitting Skill you have. Since every character should be getting double turns by the end of the game thanks to the Cheater Lumina (see below), you can spend Monoco's first turn making sure he as enough AP, then follow up immediately with Creation Void, which can only be obtained in a few locations like the Lumiere Gardens and the undersea caverns called Renoir's Drafts. Creation Void also gets bonus damage in Caster Mask, but won't get the Break Damage bonus from Joyaro outside of Almighty. While you're waiting for the Almighty Mask to come around again, focus on dealing damage and building up enemy Break Meters.\n\nBreak Damage is also a factor of actual damage, so boosting Monoco's overall output can help tremendously. Even cheap Luminas like Augmented Counter and Augmented First Strike can go a long way when paired with the Breaking Luminas mentioned above - especially when that first strike is a Skill as powerful as Creation Void! Combo Attack and Cheater can help Monoco stay ahead of his AP needs, but it's a good idea to add to his overall gain with Energising Turn.Time Tint, and Energising Stun. The latter is especially useful for Monoco, since he's going to be Stunning enemies reliably anyway. By the same token, Healing Stun and Stun Boost are worthwhile if you can afford them. ... Finding Sastro's Lost Gestrals in Clair Obscur is a scavenger hunt that takes the entire game to complete.",
