        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "For damage, you can use Moissonneuse Vendange, Portier Crash, Chevaliere Piercing, Stalact Punches, and Sakapatate Explosion which all have their uses in battle. Portier Crash is especially great when Breaking multiple enemies.\n\n\u2605 Builds: Gustave | Lune | Maelle \u2517 Sciel | Verso | Monoco \u2605 Popular: Missables | Puzzles | White Nevrons \u2517 Best Characters | Skills | Teams | Attributes \u2605 Patch 1.5.0: Verso's Drafts | Root of All Evil \u2517 Endless Tower Guide | All New Bosses \u00b7 Monoco is a playable character who gets his skills from Nevrons in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. See the best Monoco build, Monoco's best skills, attributes, weapons, and how to get all of Monoco's skills in this guide! ... The Joyaro weapon scales with the Agility and Defense attributes, which is great for Monoco. This increases his Speed and other stats thanks to Joyaro's scaling. The Pictos and Luminas give him more damage, increased Break capability, and more power to his parries. Do note that this is only for Monoco's build for Act 3. For Monoco's best skills and equipments for Act 2, check out the sections below!\n\nMonoco's best skills are a combination of support, utility, and support skills. For support, you have Potier Energy and Pelerin Heal, allowing you to heal or give allies AP as needed. Casting Potier Energy at the start is extremely recommended, as this will give your teammates more move options! For damage, Moissonneuse Vendange, Stalact Punches, and Chevaliere Piercing are your damage skills you can choose to use depending on whether you need to break, build up stagger, or bypass enemy shield. Lastly, you have Benisseur Mortar, which, on top of dealing high damage, can get you to the Almighty Wheel instantly. In Act 3, you can keep Potier Energy since its a great supportive skill. For damage, you can use Moissonneuse Vendange, Portier Crash, Chevaliere Piercing, Stalact Punches, and Sakapatate Explosion which all have their uses in battle. Portier Crash is especially great when Breaking multiple enemies.\n\nThe Nusaro is the best weapon to get for Monoco due to the insane Power and high Agility and Vitality scaling. These are stats you would want since Monoco can easily set the team up with skills like Potier Energy or deal high damage even on enemies with shields through Chevaliere Piercing. Furthermore, this weapon rewards you for parrying by allowing you to reach Almighty Wheel faster and will let you deal 30% more damage if matching the skill and the wheel, which is extremely powerful! ... In Act 3, Monoco's best weapon is Joyaro. It lets you start in Almighty Mask and gives you a consistent damage boost as long as you don't take damage. It scales well with Agility and Defense, providing him with both speed and survivability. The only problem is that the only way you can get it is by beating end game bosses in the Endless Night Sanctuary or Flying Manor areas.\n\nThe best Pictos for Monoco in Act 3 are Immaculate, Energising Parry, and Empowering Parry. This gives him a mix of health and offensive stats, along with a stacking damage boost as long as you don't get damaged. For Luminas, focus on the ones that give more AP, parry effects, Break, and more damage. This lets you strengthen Monoco's parries more while also having consistent AP generation and lets him use his damaging or supportive abilities every turn. With Patch 1.5.0, you can also use most of the damage increasing Luminas, along with AP Discount. The AP reduction is great for Monoco's Skill costs and allows you to cast more Skills in a single turn. ... Monoco shines with teammates that have the potential to deal high damage, as he can support them or match their damage capabilities for an offensive-focused team. Their synergy lies with follow-throughs rather than relying on each other's effect.",
