        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Guide for all Clair Obscur Expedition 33 Monoco Skill Locations to earn the Feet Collection trophy &amp; achievement. This shows where to find all Monoco Skills in Clair Obscur.\n\nClair Obscur: Expedition 33 contains 44 Monoco Skills required for the trophy/achievement Feet Collection. After Monoco joins your party during Act 2 of the story you can start obtaining his skills. Unlike other characters these are obtained by beating enemies while he is in the main party to get a skill similar to the enemy\u2019s attack. Since the game\u2019s launch there have been patches that made it so none of the skills are missable anymore, they can now be obtained at any time at the end of the game. If you want the easiest time getting all skills, it is recommended you keep Monoco in your main party after he joins during Act 2. You will be able to get almost all of the skills without going out of your way as you fight enemies through the rest of the story and side areas. If you want to leave it until later, you can obtain the majority of skills through the Endless Tower as it involves fights against almost every enemy in the game, or go to the listed locations below.\n\nSkills are listed in the order that they appear in the grid in Monoco\u2019s Upgrade Skills menu when viewed at an Expedition Flag. Skills are listed left to right, top to bottom along with the row/column number as they appear in the grid, along with the general earliest location you can obtain the skill (the lowest level enemy). ... Monoco starts with this skill. ... Monoco starts with this skill. ... This skill is unlocked during Monoco\u2019s battle tutorial. If you skip his tutorial, you can fight this enemy in the group of three in the area northeast of Monoco\u2019s Station. ... Group of 3 enemies on small beach along west corridor of map. ... Group of 3 enemies in the middle of the area northeast of Monoco\u2019s Station. ... Group of 3 enemies southeast of the entrance to Monoco\u2019s Station. ... Trial 1 \u2013 3, other instances of this boss don\u2019t respawn.\n\nGroup of 3 enemies southeast of the entrance to Monoco\u2019s Station. ... Group of 3 enemies southeast of Gestral Beach. ... Group of 3 enemies north of Forgotten Battlefield exit. ... Group of 3 enemies east of Forgotten Battlefield exit on the beach. ... From the flag take the path up to the right to encounter the large enemy. ... Group of three enemies on red island northwest of Old Lumiere exit. ... Group of three enemies on the lower level along the main path. ... From the flag take the leftmost path up the climbing holds. Go to either the left or right of the stairs on the upper platforms to find a rope that goes to a lower platform. Follow the grapples back toward the entrance area where you can climb another rope with this boss at the top. The other location this boss can be found on The Continent doesn\u2019t respawn. ... Along the main path, the next enemy you encounter walking around the pillar.\n\nGroup of 3 enemies in the middle of the area northeast of Monoco\u2019s Station. ... Group of 3 enemies east of Forgotten Battlefield exit on the beach. ... Crystal enemy walking around the centre of the area between Monoco\u2019s Station and Old Lumiere. ... Group of 3 enemies northwest of Painting Workshop entrance. ... Trial 2 \u2013 3, other instances of this boss don\u2019t respawn. ... Group of three enemies on small beach along west corridor of map. ... Along the main path when you encounter the light enemy with the two floating swords. ... Along the main path when you encounter the dark enemy with the two floating swords. ... Group of 3 enemies north of Boat Graveyard. ... Group of 3 enemies on small beach on west corridor of map. ... Group of 3 enemies north of Forgotten Battlefield exit. ... Group of 3 enemies southeast of the entrance to Monoco\u2019s Station.",
