      {
        "type": "knowledge",
        "title": "Monoco | Expedition 33 Wiki",
        "url": "https://expedition33.wiki.fextralife.com/Monoco",
        "metadata": {
          "type": "webpage_metadata",
          "site_domain": "fextralife.com",
          "favicon_url": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=fextralife.com",
          "site_name": "Fextralife"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "For example one of Monoco&#x27;s staring skills is Stalact Punches, which is tied to a Heavy Mask, players can use this at any time as long as he has enough AP, but it&#x27;s more effective to use the skill when the Bestial Wheel Pointer is on a Heavy Mask to further increase its damage. On the other hand, the Almighty Mask is an &quot;all-round mask&quot; which also provides the same effect by buffing all of Monoco&#x27;s skills. Upon reaching Act II of the game, Verso can start to build his relationship with his allies by spending time with them back at Camp. The primary factor in how to progress each character&#x27;s story or to increase the level is by progressing the main story of the game. Each time you complete a major objective, progress the game, or clear out any explorable locations, it&#x27;s a good practice to go back to the expeditioner&#x27;s Camp and check up on the team.\n\nMonoco is a Character in Clair Obscur Expedition 33. Monoco, a scholarly yet bloodthirsty Gestral, joins the Expedition for the sheer thrill of battle, embracing combat as meditation. Characters are various members and allies of Expedition 33 who are on a quest to stop the \"Paintress\" from painting death. These characters are mainly party members who can fight in combat and explore the world of wonders inspired by Belle \u00c9poque France. Monoco is a Gestral, a group of friendly beings who enjoy the thrill of battle and view competition as a form of meditation. As one of the few Gestrals who speak the human language, Monoco has adopted a scholarly demeanour which belies a bloodthirsty spirit. Though Gestrals are untouched by the Paintress, the prospect of combat entices Monoco to join the Expedition. I know I shouldn't grow attached to humans. Clair Obscur Expedition 33 Monoco Guide - How to Play Monoco (Build Tips) Monoco is automatically recruited during the events in Monoco's Station in\n\nMonoco is a unique Gestral that allows him to shapeshift into a Nevron and use its skills. For Monoco to learn his Skills, he must be in an active party and defeat enemies that have this unique icon next to the enemy's health bar. Upon defeating the enemy, Monoco will acquire the foot and unlocks a new skill. Moving to the unique combat mechanic, Monoco features a Bestial Wheel (see below), Monoco's skills will have designated \"turns\" that will move the Bestial Wheel pointer forward upon using the skill. The Bestial Wheel features various masks, clockwise in order Caster Mask, Agile Mask, Balanced Mask, Heavy Mask, and the Almighty Mask. Each mask, except Almighty, occurs twice in succession, for 9 total possible positions. Each Skill of Monoco is tied to specific Masks, which means that before using a skill, players should look at where the Bestial Wheel Pointer is currently on to maximize the effects of the skill.\n\nFor example one of Monoco's staring skills is Stalact Punches, which is tied to a Heavy Mask, players can use this at any time as long as he has enough AP, but it's more effective to use the skill when the Bestial Wheel Pointer is on a Heavy Mask to further increase its damage. On the other hand, the Almighty Mask is an \"all-round mask\" which also provides the same effect by buffing all of Monoco's skills. Upon reaching Act II of the game, Verso can start to build his relationship with his allies by spending time with them back at Camp. The primary factor in how to progress each character's story or to increase the level is by progressing the main story of the game. Each time you complete a major objective, progress the game, or clear out any explorable locations, it's a good practice to go back to the expeditioner's Camp and check up on the team.\n\nBefore reaching Relationship Level 3, Verso will talk to Monoco about cutting his hair. Make sure to choose the following dialogue options: ... \"Fine!\" When Monoco tells Verso \"You first then.\" to unlock the following: Samurai Haircut (Verso) and Viking Haircut (Monoco). Before upgrading your Relationship Level with Monoco to level 4, you'll have a 1v1 duel. Win the fight to acquire the following: 3x Resplendent Chroma Catalyst and 1x Recoat. At Relationship Level 4 with Monoco: Unlocks Gradient Attack for Monoco, Sanctuary. Before you can rank up to Relationship Level 6 with Monoco, you must complete his side quest, which is to accompany him to the Sacred River to resurrect Noco. Head to the Sacred River > Fight Golgra > Resurrect Noco >> return to Camp. [See Expedition 33 Map] Requires Esquie's ability to fly to reach the location. At Relationship Level 6 with Monoco: Acquire the \"Monoco\" Music Record.",
        "is_citable": true,
        "prompt_context_metadata": {
          "url": "https://expedition33.wiki.fextralife.com/Monoco",
          "search_provider": "anthropic"
        }
