      {
        "type": "knowledge",
        "title": "Clair Obscur: Expedition 33: All Monoco Skill Locations",
        "url": "https://www.dualshockers.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-all-monoco-skill-locations/",
        "metadata": {
          "type": "webpage_metadata",
          "site_domain": "dualshockers.com",
          "favicon_url": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=dualshockers.com",
          "site_name": "DualShockers"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "You should take the exit closest to the Monoco&#x27;s Station flag, where the Grandis are, to return to the overworld. Then, keep walking across the map until you find a trio of Nevrons. The Ramasseur and the Greatsword Cultist will both teach Monoco new skills. In the overworld region located between Monoco&#x27;s Station and the Forgotten Battlefield northern exit, you&#x27;ll find a trio of Nevrons, all of which teach new skills. Use the screenshot to guide yourself. You&#x27;ll see a Troubadour, a Gault, and a D\u00e9mineur just waiting to have their feet rubbed and pass on their skills to Monoco. In the same area as the previous skills, look for another trio of unsuspecting Nevrons. They&#x27;re a bit to the northwest of the Painting Workshop. Take out the Abbest and the Rocher to acquire their skills. Around the same region as previously, go to the southeast of the Painting Workshop, northeast of the Stone Quarry, to find yet another trio of Nevrons.\n\nThere are three lonely Nevrons here, so put them out of their misery and, in the process, learn the cloudy Potier's skill. Now, let's tread back to the main story. After Monoco joins your party, your next destination is the northwestern exit from the Station. In the overworld region that leads you to Old Lumi\u00e8re, you can see a Gestral Beach to the southwest if you open the World Map. If you swim with Esquie just beyond the Gestral Beach, you'll reach another shore with a Gestral Merchant and three Nevrons. The Bruler and the Chevali\u00e8re among them have some tasty feet for you. In the Old Lumi\u00e8re region, if you head all the way west, you'll spot a giant Nevron on the horizon. If you choose to fight it, it'll be accompanied by a Danseuse, who teaches a new skill to Monoco. I've seen the Danseuse in other locations, so if the Bourgeon is too tough, don't worry\u2014you'll get that beautiful dancer's foot eventually.\n\nMonoco, my favorite Gestral, is the kind of character who uses enemy skills. You might know this concept from the Blue Mage Job in Final Fantasy and other class variations across different JRPGs. ... Leveling up is just the beginning. ... To learn new skills, Monoco needs to collect enemies' feet. Yeah, he's one of those types. He learns skills simply by being in the party that defeats certain enemies in battle. In total, Monoco can learn 46 different skills, not counting Gradient Attacks. In this Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 guide, I'll show you where to find all the Nevrons that teach Monoco a skill by collecting their feet. I'll list the skills in the order I learned them in-game. So, if you want, use this guide as a walkthrough from when Monoco joins your party. To discover which enemies have skills, you need to see their HP bar, easily done by aiming at them with a weapon or targeting them with a skill.\n\nA small icon will tell you whether the monster has a skill learnable by Monoco. However, there are two annoying caveats here. First, Monoco must be in the party when the enemy is defeated. That means if by any chance the main party dies, and you win the combat with the reserve party without Monoco, he won't learn a skill. Second, if he's not in the party, the learnable skill icon won't show up besides the monster's health. In other words, you're forced to keep Monoco in our lineup all the time if you want to learn every skill seamlessly. There's an endgame area called Endless Tower where you can find many\u2014though not all\u2014enemies and bosses that teach skills to Monoco in case you don't want to be stuck with him. To help you discover which skill you're missing, below is a table simulating Monoco's skill tree in-game. Hopefully, it helps you better locate yourself and to know which skills you need to complete Monoco's arsenal: After Monoco joins your party, you'll have two exits from Monoc\n\nYou should take the exit closest to the Monoco's Station flag, where the Grandis are, to return to the overworld. Then, keep walking across the map until you find a trio of Nevrons. The Ramasseur and the Greatsword Cultist will both teach Monoco new skills. In the overworld region located between Monoco's Station and the Forgotten Battlefield northern exit, you'll find a trio of Nevrons, all of which teach new skills. Use the screenshot to guide yourself. You'll see a Troubadour, a Gault, and a D\u00e9mineur just waiting to have their feet rubbed and pass on their skills to Monoco. In the same area as the previous skills, look for another trio of unsuspecting Nevrons. They're a bit to the northwest of the Painting Workshop. Take out the Abbest and the Rocher to acquire their skills. Around the same region as previously, go to the southeast of the Painting Workshop, northeast of the Stone Quarry, to find yet another trio of Nevrons.",
        "is_citable": true,
        "prompt_context_metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.dualshockers.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-all-monoco-skill-locations/",
          "search_provider": "anthropic",
          "age": "April 24, 2025"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "knowledge",
        "title": "Monoco Skills Guide - Clair Obscur Expedition 33",
        "url": "https://maxroll.gg/clair-obscur-expedition-33/guides/monoco-skills-guide",
        "metadata": {
          "type": "webpage_metadata",
          "site_domain": "maxroll.gg",
          "favicon_url": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=maxroll.gg",
          "site_name": "Maxroll.gg"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Chevali\u00e8re Piercing - This is to deal with shielded enemies, if you&#x27;re not fighting many or have another shield breaker in the party, swap it for Lancelier Impale to slow enemies.\n\nThe Gestral Monoco is always up for a fight. He wields a staff topped with a bell. Monoco resides at his station on the continent, living with the Grandis. He is an avid collector of Nevron feet who is always willing to go on a journey with his friend Verso. It doesn't take much convincing to get Monoco to join Expedition 33 as there's plenty of fighting to be done. This guide details each of Monoco's skills, with notes on how to use them, then continues on to suggested synergies and team compositions. Monoco's unique mechanic is the Bestial Wheel. Move between different masks, each of which empowers different Nevron abilities. Each skill you use advances the wheel a certain number of steps, so you need to plan ahead to empower your desired skills. ... Unlike the other characters, Monoco does not gain skill points when leveling up. Instead, you need to defeat a Nevron with Monoco in the active party to gain its ability.\n\nIt's difficult to nail down synergies for a character that has so many possible builds. So here is an example of a build on Monoco using Grandaro with an explanation of how the 6 skills work together. The following build was made when playing the game on Expert, where enemies get frequent attacks so if you're playing on Expeditioner or Story, you would want a lower AP cost break skill. Chevali\u00e8re Piercing - This is to deal with shielded enemies, if you're not fighting many or have another shield breaker in the party, swap it for Lancelier Impale to slow enemies. Sakapatate Fire - Used during Almighty Mask to nuke the screen and leave a powerful burn. Portier Crash - Used to break enemies, or deal AoE when in Heavy mask instead of Almighty. Clair Enfeeble - Debuffs bosses for 3 turns, making it easier to survive their hits. Swap your weapon to Monocaro and use this as an opener on difficult encounters.\n\nMonoco uses Nevron skills by collecting their feet. Each skill advances the Bestial Wheel. Different masks empower each skill, enhancing them or adding new effects. There are tons of ways to build Monoco, experiment with different weapons and skills to find something that works for you. ... Added more info to Moissonneuse Vendange and Stalact Punches. Guide written for game release. This website is supported by ads.Try Maxroll Ad-Free Experience \u00b7 Getting Started in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 (Beginner's Guide) ... \u00a9 2026 Maxroll a brand of IGN Entertainment, Inc. All rights reserved. No part of this website or its content may be reproduced without the copyright owner's permission.",
        "is_citable": true,
        "prompt_context_metadata": {
          "url": "https://maxroll.gg/clair-obscur-expedition-33/guides/monoco-skills-guide",
          "search_provider": "anthropic",
          "age": "April 27, 2025"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "knowledge",
        "title": "All Monoco's Skill Locations - Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 Walkthrough - Neoseeker",
        "url": "https://www.neoseeker.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33/Monoco_Skills",
        "metadata": {
          "type": "webpage_metadata",
