          "site_name": "Neoseeker"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "While he only begins with two skills, Chalier Combo and Stalact Punches, he can be extremely powerful once you&#x27;ve unlocked more of his skills. ... Below you\u2019ll find a table with numbers corresponding to the skills in the image above.\n\nMonoco is unique among the expeditioners in terms of access to skills, as he obtains new skills by collecting the feet of defeated Nevrons from battle, rather than through Skill Points earned by leveling up. While he only begins with two skills, Chalier Combo and Stalact Punches, he can be extremely powerful once you've unlocked more of his skills. ... Below you\u2019ll find a table with numbers corresponding to the skills in the image above. While most enemies can be found in multiple areas, we'll only be listing the most common areas. That being said, if an enemy is missable, such as bosses, and appears in the Endless Tower, they will be listed by trial and stage (e.g. Endless Tower (1-3) for Trial 1 - Stage 3). ... Support our guide writers and staff so we can continue to make the best guides for all of your favourite games.",
