      {
        "type": "knowledge",
        "title": "All Monoco Skill Locations | Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 | Gamer Guides\u00ae",
        "url": "https://www.gamerguides.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33/guide/characters/playable/all-monoco-skill-locations",
        "metadata": {
          "type": "webpage_metadata",
          "site_domain": "gamerguides.com",
          "favicon_url": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=gamerguides.com",
          "site_name": "Gamer Guides"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "You can find out what we recommend for his best skills on our Best Monoco Skills Guide. The skills below are listed in the order we got them and are separated by their mask. Note that the locations listed are not the only places you can get some of these skills, as you will find a lot of the Nevrons appearing in other dungeons or other places on the world map. The location we have below will 100% direct you to a Nevron with the skill though. ... Balanced Mask skills are indicated by their red mask. Any skill in the list below will be enhanced by using them when the Bestial Wheel displays a Balanced Mask. ... Chevali\u00e8re Combo is a multi-hit attack that deals more when the Bestial Wheel displays a Balanced Mask. Caster Mask skills are indicated by their blue mask. Any skill in the list below will be enhanced by using it when the Bestial Wheel displays a Caster Mask. ... Potier Energy will transform Monoco into a Potier to replenish AP to the party.\n\nYou can find out what we recommend for his best skills on our Best Monoco Skills Guide. The skills below are listed in the order we got them and are separated by their mask. Note that the locations listed are not the only places you can get some of these skills, as you will find a lot of the Nevrons appearing in other dungeons or other places on the world map. The location we have below will 100% direct you to a Nevron with the skill though. ... Balanced Mask skills are indicated by their red mask. Any skill in the list below will be enhanced by using them when the Bestial Wheel displays a Balanced Mask. ... Chevali\u00e8re Combo is a multi-hit attack that deals more when the Bestial Wheel displays a Balanced Mask. Caster Mask skills are indicated by their blue mask. Any skill in the list below will be enhanced by using it when the Bestial Wheel displays a Caster Mask. ... Potier Energy will transform Monoco into a Potier to replenish AP to the party.\n\nMonoco is the final party member in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, and he comes with a lot of skills. However, getting these skills involves a lot of exploring, searching for Nevrons (enemies), which is where you will get them from. There are a total of 46 skills to find for Monoco, so read on to find out where to find them. ... Monoco is a Gestral who eats Nevron Feet to learn skills. If you want to jump to a specific section, click on the links below. ... When you get Monoco, you\u2019ll soon find out that Monoco has a bit of a foot fetish. Monoco gets his skills by devouring Nevron Feet. Nevrons are all the enemies you will fight throughout the game. When you come across a Nevron with a skill that you haven\u2019t got yet, you\u2019ll see the by its health bar. This means it has a skill you haven\u2019t acquired yet. ... Once you find the enemy, all you need to do is defeat it to get the skill; there isn\u2019t anything else you need to do, and the skill is a 100% drop.\n\nThat\u2019s it for Monoco\u2019s Skills. There are three more skills, which are called Gradient Attacks, but these are obtained by leveling up your relationship with Monoco. These powerful attacks can only be used when you reach Gradient levels 1, 2, or 3. However, this is a gameplay system unlocked in Act 2. ... \u201cTomorrow Comes\u201d - With only one year left to live, join Gustave, Maelle, and their fellow Expeditioners as they embark upon a desperate quest to break the Paintress\u2019 cycle of death. Follow the trail of previous expeditions and discover their fate. This guide will contain the following: A Deep dive on all Characters, including their best skills and weapons ... Get access to this feature and a lot more by upgrading to a premium account.",
        "is_citable": true,
        "prompt_context_metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.gamerguides.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33/guide/characters/playable/all-monoco-skill-locations",
          "search_provider": "anthropic",
          "age": "April 24, 2025"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "knowledge",
        "title": "All Monoco Skills In Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 (& How To Get Them)",
        "url": "https://screenrant.com/clair-obscur-how-get-all-monoco-skills/",
        "metadata": {
          "type": "webpage_metadata",
          "site_domain": "screenrant.com",
          "favicon_url": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=screenrant.com",
          "site_name": "ScreenRant"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "The Caster Skills also include Monoco&#x27;s best support skills, including Orphelin Cheers, Pelerin Heal, Potier Energy, and Troubadour Trumpet, which grants a random Buff to all allies.\n\nMonoco has nearly fifty different skills in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, and you can unlock them by defeating enemies with him in your party.\n\nBalanced Mask skills include Monoco's very first starting skill, Chalier Combo, as well as one of my favorite fire skills in his arsenal, Danseuse Waltz. You can get this earlier than Act 3 at the Endless Tower by visiting Frozen Hearts, the optional side area near Monoco's Station. I'd recommend going to the Frozen Hearts area regardless, as you can collect the Eternal Ice needed to unlock the Monoco's Station merchant's entire inventory. He has a ton of great weapons, so it's worth the trouble, and you'll get a ton of great drops in Frozen Hearts as well. Monoco's Caster Mask skills include some of the most powerful in his arsenal, such as the Creation Void attack that deals three hits of extreme Void damage. If you're facing a single enemy, this will do ridiculous amounts of damage, as each cast that hits the same enemy gets an increased damage buff.\n\nThe Caster Skills also include Monoco's best support skills, including Orphelin Cheers, Pelerin Heal, Potier Energy, and Troubadour Trumpet, which grants a random Buff to all allies. These are all skills I recommend for buffing the rest of your party with a tank support build using Monoco. Just make sure Monoco has ample Speed by increasing Agility and using Speed-boosting Pictos, or you won't be able to use these buffs often enough for them to matter. Monoco's Heavy Mask skills are the most abundant and diverse, with a range of useful support skills and offensive attacks with various elements, particularly Monoco's few Earth-based skills. These include Hexga Crush, Glaise Earthquakes, and Eveque Spear. The Grosse Tete Whack can be picked up from the option Grosse Tete boss on The Continent in front of the Coastal Cave. Get ready to parry, because this boss will just bounce on your party until it eventually explodes.\n\nMonoco is one of the quirkiest and most interesting playable characters in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, with nearly fifty unique skills that can only be acquired by collecting the feet of defeated Nevron enemies around the Continent. Monoco is the last playable character you can unlock and has a relatively limited weapon selection compared to the other main characters. However, his wide range of unlockable skills more than compensates for this and gives you a surplus of options to develop a Monoco build that fits your preferred playstyle. This article contains spoilers for Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. As soon as you unlock Monoco during Act 2, you will also unlock his very first skill by defeating the Stalact as part of the main story progression. This first interaction explains how Monoco's skills work, and you'll get a first look at Monoco's Bestial Wheel, the central feature of his combat mechanics.",
        "is_citable": true,
        "prompt_context_metadata": {
          "url": "https://screenrant.com/clair-obscur-how-get-all-monoco-skills/",
          "search_provider": "anthropic",
          "age": "May 4, 2025"
        }
