    "thinking": "Now I have a clearer picture. The sources mention these skills for Monoco's endgame:\n\nFrom Game8 (Act 3):\n- Potier Energy (support, AP to party)\n- Pelerin Heal (healing)\n- Moissonneuse Vendange (damage)\n- Portier Crash (AoE break)\n- Chevaliere Piercing (shield breaker)\n- Sakapatate Explosion (nuke in Almighty)\n- Benisseur Mortar (damage + Almighty)\n\nFrom Maxroll (example build for Expert with Grandaro):\n\n\n- Chevaliere Piercing (shielded enemies)\n- Sakapatate Fire (nuke in Almighty)\n- Portier Crash (break, AoE)\n- Clair Enfeeble (debuff bosses)\n- Monocaro weapon swap\n\nFrom Keengamer (DPS build), I'm seeing a different approach focused on single-target nukes and scaling damage\u2014Creation Void and Duallist Storm for burst, Lampmaster Light for AoE that builds over time, and Chapelier Slash for setting up crits and marks.\n\nFor Monoco specifically as an AP battery and support breaker, the skill priority shifts toward Potier Energy first for party AP, then breaking tools, Pelerin Heal for sustain, and damage options like Benisseur Mortar or Moissonneuse Vendange to reach Almighty thresholds. The reality is there's no single \"best 6\"\u2014it really depends on whether I'm building for support, pure DPS, or break focus.",
