    "text": "The sources don't converge on a single definitive six-skill list for Monoco the way they do for other characters \u2014 his 46-skill pool and the Bestial Wheel mean the optimal six depends heavily on the role you're building for. Here's what sources consistently highlight, split by orientation:\n\n**Support/AP battery** (your current role):\n- **Potier Energy** \u2014 AP to party, consistently cited as his most important skill\n- **Pelerin Heal** \u2014 party heal\n- **Moissonneuse Vendange** \u2014 damage, already have it\n- **Benisseur Mortar** \u2014 high damage + instant Almighty Mask\n- **Abbest Wind** \u2014 low-cost mask-skipping (get to Almighty faster)\n- **Chevaliere Piercing** \u2014 shield bypass\n\n**DPS/Break build** (what sources recommend with Joyaro endgame):\n- **Creation Void** \u2014 massive single-target Void damage with scaling per consecutive hit on the same target\n- **Duallist Storm** \u2014 extreme single-target with Break potential, recommended as the opener in Almighty\n- **Lampmaster Light** \u2014 AoE light damage that scales over multiple casts\n- **Portier Crash** \u2014 Break + AoE in Heavy Mask\n- **Potier Energy** \u2014 still included even in DPS builds for AP flow\n- **Chevaliere Piercing** or **Chalier Combo** \u2014 flex slot\n\n**Honest caveat:** Monoco isn't in your endgame team (Maelle/Sciel/Verso is), so this is academic unless you're planning Flying Manor post-game. Also, several sources note that in Act 3, Monoco quickly becomes less useful compared to more specialised party members \u2014 the consensus seems to be that he shines in the mid-game role you're already using him for, rather than the endgame.",
