        "text": "To find the Chromatic Danseuse, you must finish the Old Lumiere mission in Act 2 first. You can return later or fight it straight away. However, the party should be at least Level 33 before attempting this optional boss fight.\n\nMany optional boss fights in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 are as challenging as the main story bosses, if not more so. The Chromatic Danseuse is a dangerous optional boss that manifests two more mirror versions of itself, so you're essentially fighting three at once. It alternates between fire and ice, as well as attack and defense. On top of that, it's extremely difficult to parry and dodge when it strikes multiple times in succession, and it can do a lot of damage. The Chromatic Danseuse can be easily overlooked, as players must return to a prior area in the story in order to encounter it. For those looking to take it on, here's how to locate and defeat the Chromatic Danseuse in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. To find the Chromatic Danseuse, you must finish the Old Lumiere mission in Act 2 first. You can return later or fight it straight away. However, the party should be at least Level 33 before attempting this optional boss fight.\n\nThe Chromatic Danseuse is a fast and powerful adversary that will summon two clones to fight alongside it. Their element-based attacks are just as dangerous, and they also switch between fire and ice stances, sometimes in opposition to the original Chromatic Danseuse. The enemies will target one member of the party with a series of ice and fire attacks, depending on their stance. Their ice attacks can inflict freeze status. After freezing a party member, all three enemies will attempt a Gradient attack, which deals massive damage. So, ensure that at least one party member doesn't have a fire or ice-based weapon. The Chromatic Danseuse's attacks are difficult to parry due to their speed, so try dodging if you're having trouble getting the timing right. In the likely event that a party member gets frozen, ensure the team has the Healing Share and Cleansing Tint Luminas active.\n\nThe Chromatic Danseuse will absorb and heal when the party uses the same element in fire or ice stances to attack them. To defeat the Chromatic Danseuse, avoid attacking the clones other than using regular and Gradient Parries. The Chromatic Danseuse can summon more if you kill them. Focus all the party's attacks on the middle one. It's a good idea to mark it first and then attack with Verso's Blitz, which can deal 9999 damage and grant him another turn. Verso's Gradient Attack, Sabotage, can inflict up to 9999 damage and mark all enemies for damage. Use Lune's strongest elemental attacks to combat the fire or ice stances. When the Chromatic Danseuse eventually falls, you'll still have to deal with the remaining clones. Thankfully, their HP is much lower than that of the original, so finish them off accordingly.",
