wing, translucent robes that appear to ripple and shift as if made of light or mist. The creature's skin is pale and almost glowing, with long, flowing hair that gives it a spectral look. Enemies feature a variety of hostile characters that players will encounter throughout their journey. These enemies come in different shapes and sizes, and have different attack styles and patterns. When fighting this enemy, it can switch stances depending on the element you attack it with. If it has a blue \"aura\" around it, then it is weak against Fire Damage and can absorb Ice Damage. When a Fire-damaging skill or weapon is used against the Danseuses, it will change its stance to Fire, making it weak to Ice Damage and it can absorb Fire damage. Players can encounter this enemy in a group with an Obscur in the Tainted Hearts section inside The Monolith, defeating this group for the first time will reward you with the Braselim.\n\nClair Obscur Expedition 33 Danseuses NPC notes, tips, lore details, and more go here. Join the page discussion Tired of anon posting? Register! ... if you don't kill the one on the left position/their right position, it will not spawn a clone. So kill the other 2 first, and it will spam the clone spawn but fail ... I'm kinda hold in the frozen hearts because they are waaaay too strong for me. I ve been doin xp for hours before fightin the duelliste, he was very easy but now, the very next ennemy is too strong. How's possible. Is it a path i'm not supposed to go just after monoco ? ... Another thing to mention is that this enemy can sometimes spawn mini clones of its self. I've only seen this once after roughly 10 encounters so it is rare. ... what outfit resembles this enemy?",
