        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "After defeating Renoir, you&#x27;ll ... and destroyed all those buildings earlier in Act 2. Nearby, you&#x27;ll find the Train Station Ruins Expedition Flag and will be able to locate the Chromatic Danseuse enemy not far down that same ...\n\nOnce you find the Chromatic Danseuse, you'll need to understand how its attacks work in order to reap the rewards. The Chromatic Danseuse has a unique ability to spawn two clones at the start of any turn if it doesn't have any active clones. The fight will not end until all enemies are killed, and killing each of these clones rewards 5x Colour of Lumina. If you haven't caught on yet, that means you can theoretically continue killing the Danseuse clones and skipping your turn forever, avoiding the Chromatic Danseuse until you (or your system) can't do it anymore. ... Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 is packed full of incredible yet tragic narrative moments, with characters that you can't help but fall in love with. ... There's supposedly a further method for increasing your rewards for this glitch involving the Contorso weapon, which some players on Reddit and other channels have reported doubles your XP, Chroma, and even the Colour of Lumina rewards.\n\nIf you want to get your hands on the secret Baguette weapons in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, you might want to hang on to those festival tokens. ... It's also hard to imagine the developers intended for players to be able to earn over a billion points of XP in a single fight, even if it is a great feeling to walk away with a fully decked-out Level 99 crew after an hour or so of cheesing the Chromatic Danseuse. Either way, at least for the time being, you can push your system and your patience to the limits by spawning as many Danseuse clones as you can take down, potentially earning upwards of a billion XP and thousands of Colour of Lumina in a single fight. While the above exploit is likely to get patched out, there are plenty of other ways to farm both XP and Colour of Lumina. Notably, there are some specific enemies throughout Act 3 that reliably drop Colour of Lumina after you've killed them the first time.\n\nTo farm the most possible Colour of Lumina in Clair Obscur from a single enemy, you will need to make it about halfway through the game and finish the main story up to the Manor in Old Lumiere. After defeating Renoir, you'll be able to go back and freely explore, and you can actually head back to the spot where Monoco messed up big time and destroyed all those buildings earlier in Act 2. Nearby, you'll find the Train Station Ruins Expedition Flag and will be able to locate the Chromatic Danseuse enemy not far down that same path. Old Lumiere is well worth fully exploring again after you've defeated Renoir there, with a handful of areas only accessible after the fight. This Chromatic Danseuse enemy is your one-stop shop for a motherlode of Colour of Lumina upgrade materials. Thanks to one particular skill this enemy has, you can stack thousands of Colour of Lumina during this encounter, but it's imperative that you don't kill the Chromatic Danseuse until you are ready to cash out for go\n\nThere's an enemy in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 that might be a glitch, but it's easily the best Colour of Lumina and XP farm - until they patch it.",
