        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Chromatic Danseuse optional boss. From the right street flag turn around and climb the rope, on your left there is a new area opened Train Station Ruins and a new flag. The boss is after the flag.\n\nSince there's no page for the Chromatic Danseuse I'll put it here. You can endlessly farm the clones that the Chromatic Danseuse summons and they drop 3 Color of Lumina each. I worked on it for about a hour and came out with over 1200 CoL. ... There are several things that unlock after you defeat Renoir In the Manor Gardens from the flag run straight ahead and to the left there you can see a path follow the path and there is a rope down to an Expedition Journal 42. Also in the manor gardens running from the flag this time on the right there is a path that leads to a Paint Cage then carry on past the cage follow the path up around the cliffs onto a building into the distance and then use the structures to climb up the cliff for the Healing Death Pictos. On Right street follow the path to the end after the last enemy there will be climbing structures on the wall, climb up and follow the path for the Mime.\n\nOld Lumiere is a Location in Clair Obscur Expedition 33. Old Lumiere Guide: All Characters, All Checkpoints, Enemies, Bosses, Items, and more for Expedition 33.\n\nFinally, from the entrance flag, run straight ahead and stay right at any branch point and you'll reach a previously-inaccessible point, the Train Station Ruins. Beyond this flag lies a challenging optional boss, Chromatic Danseuse. Note: this boss will summon clones indefinitely so long as it remains alive & each clone will provide XP & drop 5 Color of Lumina and a chance of dropping a Polished Chrome Catalyst when killed. This can be used to farm a potentially unlimited amount of Lumina to expand your active Pictos for late game encounters. Notes, Tips, and other Trivia for Old Lumiere Location go here. ... Join the page discussion Tired of anon posting? Register! ... The explanation is very garbage, but you get a 1/10 for effort. Please, consider writing with comprehension next time, author. ... When I entered the manor bathroom I noticed a picture of a dog on a shelf in the corner.\n\nChromatic Danseuse optional boss. From the right street flag turn around and climb the rope, on your left there is a new area opened Train Station Ruins and a new flag. The boss is after the flag. ... fast travel the right street and follow the way, there is a mime boss there and you end up returning gardens ... You can actually cheese your way to the Time Tint pictos by jumping the rocks before that crawlspace to the chroma (in fact I was able to jump cheese a lot of items by doing this in different places (not that these places are hard to get to, but sometimes it's short, especially when you have to drop down to ledges and can't get back up ... The section with the crawl to the Chroma also has a pictos 'Time Tint' you need to go up the main walkway then jump down onto ledge. ... if you enter this location after fighting Renoir, there would be also a side path leading to Chromatic Danseuse boss",
