        "text": "She can also summon clones, making the fight feel unfair and brutal. Found past the Train Station Ruins Expedition Flag (Old Lumiere), the Chromatic Danseuse is a test of patience, but importantly, it is a test to see how well you c\n\nIn this guide, we shall go over how to beat the Chromatic Danseuse in Clair Obscur Expedition 33, one of the harder bosses in the game. Clair Obscur Expedition 33: How To Beat Chromatic Danseuse (Source: Kepler Interactive) The Continent in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 is a haunting blend of brutality and serenity. The inhabitants of this world are beautiful, yet step up close and they will tear you to shreds in moments. This is a fate that befell all the past expeditions, and you are here to defy it. The Chromatic Danseuse is one such boss that intertwines beauty with violence. The enigmatic boss uses the grace of dance to attack you, making her hauntingly beautiful. The dance moves make her difficult to read, adding to the chaos of her already high damage. She can also summon clones, making the fight feel unfair and brutal. Found past the Train Station Ruins Expedition Flag (Old Lumiere), the Chromatic Danseuse is a test of patience, but importantly, it is a test to see how well you c\n\nThe flashy lights and dance moves embolden the attacks, but look past, and you\u2019ll see predictable attack patterns. If you\u2019re struggling and need help in beating the boss, we\u2019re here to help. In this guide, we shall go over how to beat the Chromatic Danseuse in Clair Obscur Expedition 33. Related: How To Defeat the Dualliste in Clair Obscur Expedition 33 \u00b7 The Chromatic Danseuse (Source: Kepler Interactive, 100% Guides/YouTube) Also Read: Clair Obscur Expedition 33: How To Beat Sorrowful Chapelier \u00b7 The Chromatic Danseuse has two stances that she uses while fighting you \u2013 the Fire stance and the Ice stance. When in Fire stance, the boss is weak to Ice but will absorb Fire attacks to heal. In Ice Stance, the boss is weak to Fire but will absorb the Ice attacks to heal. You have to switch your offense based on what stance the boss assumes. The boss will also summon two clones early on into the fight.",
