        "text": "Agility, Vitality, and Might are your main focus but it\u2019s still important to have high crit chance. Do not invest points into anything else. Luck can further enhance Lune\u2019s critical hit consistency and elemental skill effectiveness, making ...\n\nVitality is the second priority because Kralim scales with it as well. Might is your third priority to boost raw damage. Base attack is a foundational stat that influences Lune\u2019s damage output and interacts with weapon scaling, making it crucial for maximizing her potential. Use your highest Crit Chance Pictos to raise Crit Chance as high as possible for maximum damage. Critical rate is especially important for maximizing Lune\u2019s damage, particularly when using skills like Elemental Trick and weapons or Pictos that benefit from high crit chances. Agility, Vitality, and Might are your main focus but it\u2019s still important to have high crit chance. Do not invest points into anything else. Luck can further enhance Lune\u2019s critical hit consistency and elemental skill effectiveness, making it a valuable attribute in late-game builds. The recommended endgame Attributes for the Archmage Lune Build are: ...\n\nEndgame combo logic stays the same: build toward Lightning Dance or Elemental Genesis, but how you do it changes. With Kralim, you get two random stains when you have none. Because they are random you will either want to start with Terraquake, Wildfire or Ice Lance depending on what stains you need next. Sometimes they\u2019ll both be the same, which can lock you out of Genesis, but it\u2019s worth it \u2013 Kralim is one of the best weapons in the game. Advanced strategies in the late game allow Lune to cast hell repeatedly by optimizing AP management, stains, and pictograms, resulting in massive damage output. The hell skill is especially important for late-game damage, as it can be spammed for devastating results when combined with the right setup. Using the energy master pictogram or skill provides extra AP, enabling powerful combos like casting Hell or Elemental Genesis every turn.\n\nLastly swap out Crustal Crush for Terraquake. Terraquake helps with breaking and still does solid damage while generating Earth Stains. It\u2019s especially good if you pair Lune with Verso or Monoco who are the best breakers in the game. Endgame, it\u2019s all about Kralim. You can get it before Act 1 ends if you\u2019re very good, but it will be hard. Still, it\u2019s worth the grind \u2013 Kralim is Lune\u2019s best weapon for this build and arguably one of the best in the entire game. It scales with Agility and adds Electricity as an element, which is rarely resisted. Kralim gives three powerful effects: Bonus damage for rotating elements (up to +80%). Generates 2 stains when empty \u2013 amazing for lunes opening turns. +1 AP per stain consumed \u2013 solves all AP issues. Combined with Cheater and First Strike, Lune often gets three actions before enemies can move once.\n\nIf you aim the slow at the right enemy, you can manipulate turn order to let a teammate leapfrog ahead. Turn order is king in this game \u2013 if your characters can act before the enemy, then you will not have to worry about dodging, increasing your survival which will in turn increase your damage output. Use this when you feel you have enough AP generation on Lune and no longer need Thermal Transfer. Elemental Genesis, deals Lightning Dance-level damage but in an AoE. It requires one stain of each element, which makes it harder to obtain, but this build is designed to make that easier. If you\u2019re fighting a group of strong enemies, build toward Genesis. If it\u2019s a single boss, go Lightning Dance. Lightning Dance is much easier to prepare until you get the Kralim weapon. Crustal Crush is our last skill and is great for breaking tougher enemies, which becomes important later on.",
        "is_citable": true,
