        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Trebuchim is Lune&#x27;s best weapon in Act 1 thanks to its Level 4 Passive skill and its Vitality and Luck scaling giving Lune survivability and damage. The free Stains that Lune gets from her Free Aim shots helps Lune strengthen her Skills early. Once you reach Act 2, Kralim will be your weapon, especially if you want to use Lune as your main DPS. It increases Lune&#x27;s damage as long as you use a different element with each spell cast, while also providing Lune with free Stains if she do not have any. It also recovers 1 AP whenever Lune use a Stain. For Act 3, give Lune Choralim, as its strong Level 10 Passive works well with Pictos and Luminas that give extra turns, while its Level 20 Passive is great for Lune&#x27;s skills with multiple hits, especially if her Crit Rate is at 100%. ... The skills above take advantage of Lune&#x27;s Stain mechanic to constantly deal increased damage.\n\nLune is a playable character who uses the Lunerim in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. See Lune's best builds, weapon, attributes, playstyle, skills, and character profile here! ... The values in red are the ones to be prioritized. Act 1 is calculated with 45 points at level 15. Act 2 is calculated with 90 points at level 30. Act 3 is calculated with 180 points at level 60. Lune's best attributes in Act 1 are Vitality and Luck since Lune's best weapon at that point of the game is Trebuchim. Putting most of Lune's attribute points to Vitality and Luck will increase Lune's damage and survivability early on. In Act 1, also put some of Lune's attribute points into Agility and Defense to further increase Lune's survivability and Speed. Lastly, put the remaining points into Might for more damage. Once you reach Act 2, swap to Kralim and then respec Lune's attribute points.\n\nTrebuchim is Lune's best weapon in Act 1 thanks to its Level 4 Passive skill and its Vitality and Luck scaling giving Lune survivability and damage. The free Stains that Lune gets from her Free Aim shots helps Lune strengthen her Skills early. Once you reach Act 2, Kralim will be your weapon, especially if you want to use Lune as your main DPS. It increases Lune's damage as long as you use a different element with each spell cast, while also providing Lune with free Stains if she do not have any. It also recovers 1 AP whenever Lune use a Stain. For Act 3, give Lune Choralim, as its strong Level 10 Passive works well with Pictos and Luminas that give extra turns, while its Level 20 Passive is great for Lune's skills with multiple hits, especially if her Crit Rate is at 100%. ... The skills above take advantage of Lune's Stain mechanic to constantly deal increased damage.\n\nLune's best early game weapon, Trebuchim, synergizes well with her Skills as it provides one random Stain when you perform a Free Aim shot, allowing you to cast an empowered Skill and start the Skill Chain. Healing Light will provide some support to the team as one of the earliest Healing skills, while Thermal Transfer will help Lune regenerate AP whenever the enemy is Burning. Once you reach Act 2, you can swap out Lune's Immolation for Wildfire and Electrify for Thunderfall. This lets Lune deal more damage while also making it easier for her to hit the 4 Stain requirement for Mayhem. In Act 3, as Lune have access to even more AP generating Pictos and Luminas, Lune can use her more powerful Skills such as Rockslide, Lightning Dance, Crippling Tsunami, and Rockslide. Start fights with Elemental Trick one of each Stain, then use them to either cast an empowered version of the previously mentioned skills, or cast the powerful Elemental Genesis.\n\nLune's Pictos gives her strong passive Skills. Burning Shots, for example, can apply Burn on enemies, which Lune can then take advantage of with skills like Thermal Transfer. Versatile, on the other hand, increases the power of her Base Attack whenever she performs a Free Aim shot, while SOS Shell provides some survivability. Additionally, the equipped Pictos give Lune Speed, Critical Rate, and Defense, the Stats that she needs the most in the early game. Lune's mid game Pictos and Luminas revolve around giving her as much AP as possible from numerous sources, including Parrying, Dodging, and at the start of battle. The Luminas also give Lune a lot of survivability, which she will need to counteract the side effect of Perilous Parry. Lune's Pictos prioritize giving her Critical Rate so that Elemental Trick can provide Stains, while also synergizing well with Choralim's Level 20 Passive.",
