        "text": "Best endgame Lune weapon, with ... you can cast Hell T1 and guarantee 4 stains + AOE burn, T2 you can either cast genesis to clear, terraquake to set up breaks, tsunami for AOE slow or boosted lightning dance for single target burst...\n\nBest endgame Lune weapon, with Cheater and enough AP generation you can cast Hell T1 and guarantee 4 stains + AOE burn, T2 you can either cast genesis to clear, terraquake to set up breaks, tsunami for AOE slow or boosted lightning dance for single target burst. ... Most likely the best Line weapon on balance. I think Colim can beat it over long fights (and if you're lucky) with infinite light stains, but nothing beats the simplicity and consistency of Kralim. Being able to cast Lightning Dance or Elemental Genesis every other turn is completely nuts. Just remember to load up on AP generation. ... Best weapon for lune. This plus any 2stain generating skill, combo with cheater is a 1 turn elemental genesis nuke ... If you spam elemental trick and elemental genesis, I think this weapon is better than Colim. ... Best weapon for Lune. ... This is Exp33's Blasphemous Blade.\n\nKralim is a Weapon in Clair Obscur Expedition 33. Kralim is a weapon for Lune, its base attack deals Lightning damage and scales with Vitality and Agility. When using this weapon, Lune must switch between using Skills of different elements to trigger the stacking effect of 20% bonus damage to all other elements, the effect resets if she casts a skill of the element that was used since last reset/start of combat. ... This weapon can drop from initially defeating a group of enemies in The Continent. ... Received as a reward drop from defeating the Chromatic Orphelin. ... The level 4 effect stacks additively with itself. The reset condition counts all skills used since the last time the bonus was reset, not just the last skill used \u00b7 Each element used is tracked since the last reset (or start of combat), and the bonus will continue to stack until a skill is used that matches an element previously used since the last reset of the bonus.\n\nClair Obscur Expedition 33 Lune Guide - How to Play Lune (Build Tips) This weapon will randomly give you two stains in turn start if you don't have stains, so one of the strategy is equip some skill which is gain two more stains, then you can use Elemental Genesis in secone round (except you gain two same stains by Kralim). Join the page discussion Tired of anon posting? Register! ... lvl 29 Kralim drops from the same enemies that drop Glaceso lvl 29. On the continent, needs flying, south of Painting Workshop entrance. ... Does anyone know if Kralim's lvl 4 reset if spells like typhoon, Terraquake storm caller and Fire rage activate at the beginning of every turn ? ... My testing showed Kralim L4 buff only works once per fight. If you reset you cant activate the buff ever again. So the weapon may not perform as well as expected.\n\nElemental Trick always deals Ice damage first, so it always counts as an Ice skill. Elemental Genesis will count as whichever element it randomly hits with first. Hits after the first do not count for incrementing the bonus or for resetting it, regardless of element. For multi-element skills, the accrued damage bonus is only applied to elements previously cast in the sequence since last reset, as well as the first element applied by the multi-hit ability. For example, Fire -> Lightning -> Elemental Trick would only apply the bonus to Fire, Lightning, and Ice (since Elemental Trick always starts with Ice), meaning the Earth hits of Elemental Trick would not receive a damage bonus in this sequence. The magnitude of this bonus is based on previous skills used, however, so in the above sequence, Fire, Lightning, and Ice would all receive a 40% damage bonus (two prior skills used, the Fire and Lightning), even though the bonus is also applied to the first element from the multi-element skil",
