        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Break the damage cap with Trick + Genesis, Hell, and back-to-back turns. Lune becomes an endgame nuker with explosive elemental burst.\n\nBreak the damage cap with Trick + Genesis, Hell, and back-to-back turns. Lune becomes an endgame nuker with explosive elemental burst. ... Lune Build Guide \u2013 Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies | Clair Obscur: Expedition 33Early Game Lune Build (Acts 1-2)Mid-Game Lune Build (Acts 2-3)Late-Game Lune Build (Act 3+ and NG+)Best Lune Weapons and Gear SetupBest Lune Pictos and Lumina SetupAdvanced Lune Tips, Team Synergies, and Final Strategies ... In the late game, Lune evolves into a powerhouse with unmatched AoE potential and utility. With the right Lumina setup and upgraded gear, she can loop turns, wipe out groups with Genesis or Hell, and sustain herself and the party through healing and buffs. This section focuses on builds that reach damage caps, abuse AP stacking, and play Lune as either the main carry or a devastating support-DPS hybrid. Strengths: Turn looping with Cheater, massive AoE nukes with Hell and Genesis, powerful healing options, multiple free turns via Thermal Transfe\n\nLune Build Guide \u2013 Best Skills, Weapons, and Strategies | Clair Obscur: Expedition 33Early Game Lune Build (Acts 1-2)Mid-Game Lune Build (Acts 2-3)Late-Game Lune Build (Act 3+ and NG+)Best Lune Weapons and Gear SetupBest Lune Pictos and Lumina SetupAdvanced Lune Tips, Team Synergies, and Final Strategies ... Alex is a gaming enthusiast who covers everything from the latest news and trailers to in-depth guides and gameplay tips for AAA titles. Whether it\u2019s breaking updates or strategic walkthroughs, he delivers content that keeps readers informed and ready to dive into their next game.",
