          "site_name": "Game Rant"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "One of her best builds in E33 is in Burn teams, where she can apply a lot of Burn DoTs and consume them to deal more damage. Lune has several weapons that enhance her Burn mechanics in Expedition 33, but Bonbim is the best among them.\n\nPlayers can build Lune in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 as a reliable healer or powerful DPS; here's how to build Lune.\n\nUpdated on December 15, 2025, by Nahda Nabiilah: Lune is easily one of the best characters in E33. She has a wide variety of skills that make her useful in any situation for any team. That also means that Lune can enjoy many builds based on the role she's playing in her team. With the game dropping some new items that match Lune's gameplay, this guide will be updated to add an endgame Lune build in Expedition 33. The best early build for Lune in Clair Obscur Expedition 33 revolves around the support role, mostly because Maelle is a potent early-game DPS. Lune can continuously heal her allies, which is rare among the other characters in the early game. Unfortunately, it\u2019s hard to find a healing weapon or Luminas in the early game, but that doesn\u2019t change how useful this Lune Expedition 33 build is. Having a sustain character in the team is crucial in the early game since it simplifies every combat encounter.\n\nMonoco has a strange way of earning new Skills in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. Learn how to get all of his moves in this Feet Collection guide. ... That Lune build doesn\u2019t mean she can\u2019t deal damage. In fact, Lune is one of the best DPS in Clair Obscur Expedition 33. But, it\u2019s better to build Lune as a DPS in the endgame, where more materials and items are available to support her damage. Lune is an AoE monster when it comes to endgame damage in Clair Obscur Expedition 33. She can still be very useful with her supportive build, especially because of the extra weapons and Luminas that further improve her performance. Not only that, but players can also build Lune with Typhoon. A Skill that will continuously heal allies while dealing high Ice damage to all enemies. However, it\u2019s better to build Lune as a hybrid DPS who can both destroy enemies and heal allies.\n\nOther than her AoE strong attacks, Lune can have some Skills that add utility to the team, such as Wildfire, Crippling Tsunami, and Revitalization. Wildfire is an AoE upgraded version of Immolation, and it applies Burn on enemies. As for Crippling Tsunami, it\u2019s an AoE attack that applies Slow. Lune excels in the endgame because of the variety of utility and damage she can offer. One of her best builds in E33 is in Burn teams, where she can apply a lot of Burn DoTs and consume them to deal more damage. Lune has several weapons that enhance her Burn mechanics in Expedition 33, but Bonbim is the best among them. It increases her Critical Rate, making it easier to consistently apply Burn with each attack. Players can further support this by equipping Luminas that improve Burn application, allowing Lune and her team to stack a high number of Burn DoTs on enemies.",
