          "site_name": "FandomWire"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "So, to make the most of her skills, here\u2019s what you need: Ice Lance (in place of Thermal Transfer): It slows down enemies and deals Ice Damage. Plus, it also generates Stains, something that Thermal Transfer is unable to do.\n\nLune's exceptional set of elemental abilities in Expedition 33 can be made even better by combining it with Kralim, one of the game's best weapons. ... Lune is an expert Mage in Expedition 33 and she boasts an impressive amount of elemental skills and abilities. Pairing her set of abilities up with Kralim, her best weapon, can prove to be a deadly combo. YouTuber RedGael has discovered a Nuclear build for Lune that is capable of one-shotting bosses. ... Join 100K+ fans and never miss breaking news, fan theories, trailers & exclusive content. Lune in Clair: Obscur Expedition 33 is an impressive Mage who can use elemental abilities to squander bosses with ease. But for her abilities to synergise and work in harmony, you need to know what to use and when. Don\u2019t worry, the game will tell you all about it. But what the game won\u2019t spoon-feed you is how to create the right build with her.\n\nYouTuber RedGael has created an insane Nuclear build for Lune in Expedition 33 that is capable of one-shotting bosses and dealing massive amounts of damage. For the build, one of the main requirements is that you need to have Kralim as it scales with Vitality and Agility in addition to dealing Lightning damage. Combining Lune\u2019s Mage expertise and Kralim\u2019s lightning is the stepping stone for building the Nuclear build. While Lune already has her Stains, to use them to their full potential, she\u2019ll need a lot of skills early on in Expedition 33, such as the ones listed below. Ice Lance: It deals Ice damage and slows down enemies. Wildfire: This skill sets enemies on fire and inflicts burn damage over time. Lightning Dance: An extremely powerful skill that needs to be empowered with Fire, Ice and Earth Stains to deal the maximum amount of damage.\n\nFor the most optimal combo, start off with Lune\u2019s Wildfire skill, then do a Thermal Transfer and finish it off with Lightning Dance. This will get you through most of the fights during Acts 1 and 2 and make your journey to Act 3 much easier with Lune. As for the Pictos, the YouTuber has already shared an intricate guide on what Pictos you\u2019ll need in both the early and late game and where you can get them to mow through every boss in Expedition 33. ... Luminas like Augmented First Strike, Breaking Attack, Burrn Affinity, and Critical Burn will be crucial in Acts 1 and 2. However, once you move to Act 3, make sure to grab Luminas like Painted Power, Cheater, and Charging Critical. Make sure to refer to the docs while making this build. While Lighterim is the recommended weapon for Acts 1 and 2, it\u2019s best to go for Kralim before Act 1 ends, and it won\u2019t be easy to get it in any way, since you\u2019ll need to defeat the Chromatic Orphelin boss in Yellow Harvest.\n\nSo, get out there, defeat Chromatic Orphelin and take what\u2019s yours, Kralim in this case, if you want to progress Expedition 33 like a madman and obliterate every boss, even the optional ones with Lune\u2019s spells. ... In Act 3 of Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, Lune pairs up extremely well with Maelle and Verso, but she\u2019s still more than capable enough to stand on her own two legs to face bosses head-on. So, to make the most of her skills, here\u2019s what you need: Ice Lance (in place of Thermal Transfer): It slows down enemies and deals Ice Damage. Plus, it also generates Stains, something that Thermal Transfer is unable to do. Terraquake (in place of Crustal Crush): It helps in breaking tough enemies while also generating Earth Stains \u00b7 In terms of combos, it\u2019s more or less the same as the previous Acts, but now that you have Kralim at your disposal, you get two random Stains.",
