        "text": "For Lune, use the Choralim weapon while focusing on the Agility and Defense attributes. This increases her speed and gives her more survivability. The Pictos and Luminas give her more damage and synergize with Burns.\n\n\u2605 Builds: Gustave | Lune | Maelle \u2517 Sciel | Verso | Monoco \u2605 Popular: Missables | Puzzles | White Nevrons \u2517 Best Characters | Skills | Teams | Attributes \u2605 Patch 1.5.0: Verso's Drafts | Root of All Evil \u2517 Endless Tower Guide | All New Bosses \u00b7 Here are the best character builds in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33. See early, mid, and late game builds here! ... For Gustave, use the Abysseram weapon while focusing on the Vitality and Agility attributes. This increases his Health and Speed, allowing him to take a lot of turns and be more tanky at the same time. The Pictos and Luminas let him inflict debuffs on the enemies. ... For Maelle, use the Medalum weapon while focusing on the Defense and Agility attributes. This increases her Speed and Defense while raising her Attack and Crit thanks to the attribute scaling. The Pictos and Luminas give more offensive stats and strengthen her parries, including a big damage boost for not getting hit.\n\nLunerim \u00b7 Troubadim \u00b7 Trebuchim \u00b7 Deminerim \u00b7 Benisim \u00b7 Chapelim \u00b7 Colim \u00b7 Potierim \u00b7 Kralim \u00b7 Scaverim \u00b7 Braselim \u00b7 Elerim \u00b7 Snowim \u00b7 Lithelim \u00b7 Angerim \u00b7 Betelim \u00b7 Choralim \u00b7 Coralim \u00b7 Painerim \u00b7 Redalim \u00b7 Saperim \u00b7 Bonbim \u00b7 Cleim \u00b7 Esquim \u00b7 Abysseram \u00b7 Lanceram \u00b7 Cruleram \u00b7 Noahram \u00b7 Sakaram \u00b7 Gaulteram \u00b7 Demonam \u00b7 Contorso \u00b7 Delaram \u00b7 Dualiso \u00b7 Glaceso \u00b7 Sireso \u00b7 Verleso \u00b7 Chevalam \u00b7 Danseso \u00b7 Gesam \u00b7 Dreameso \u00b7 Cultam \u00b7 Blodam \u00b7 Confuso \u00b7 Corpeso \u00b7 Liteso \u00b7 Nosaram \u00b7 Seeram \u00b7 Simoso \u00b7 Tireso \u00b7 Esquiso \u00b7 Sucreso \u00b7 Scieleson \u00b7 Algueron \u00b7 Chation \u00b7 Lusteson \u00b7 Ramasson \u00b7 Rangeson \u00b7 Sadon \u00b7 Tisseron \u00b7 Blizzon \u00b7 Martenon \u00b7 Hevason \u00b7 Bourgelon \u00b7 Garganon \u00b7 Charnon \u00b7 Corderon \u00b7 Direton \u00b7 Guleson \u00b7 Litheson \u00b7 Minason \u00b7 Moisson \u00b7 Gobluson \u00b7 Duollison \u00b7 Esquion \u00b7 Sucetton \u00b7 Nusaro \u00b7\n\nFor Lune, use the Choralim weapon while focusing on the Agility and Defense attributes. This increases her speed and gives her more survivability. The Pictos and Luminas give her more damage and synergize with Burns. This also goes well with Choralim's ability to apply Burns upon critting. ... For Sciel, use the Charnon weapon while focusing on the Luck and Defense attributes. This increases her survivability while also increasing her other stats thanks to the weapon's scaling. The Pictos and Luminas give her a lot of offensive stats, damage boosts, and AP recovery. ... For Verso, use the Chevalam weapon while focusing on the Agility and Luck attributes. This increases his Speed and Crit chance while also allowing him to start at S Rank immediately. The Pictos and Luminas give him a lot of damage boosts and strengthen his parries in exchange for being unable to be healed.",
