          "site_name": "EthuGamer"
        },
        "is_missing": false,
        "text": "Excellent nuke for endgame mobs or bosses. Thermal Transfer Low Ice damage. If the enemy is Burning, Lune gains 4 AP. With 2 Earth Stains, she gets a second turn. Best AP regeneration tool in her kit. Healing Light Restores HP and clears debuffs from an ally. Consuming 2 Earth Stains makes it free. Reliable support with minimal cost. Rebirth Revives an ally and grants AP. Requires 3 Lightning Stains to remove the AP cost. Must-have for late-game sustain. ... Openers: Start fights with Elemental Trick or Earth Rising to begin building your Stains pool. Mid-fight Utility: If allies are low or enemies are applying pressure, switch to Healing Light or Thermal Transfer for tempo recovery. Burst Phase: Use Hell or Lightning Dance when Stains align and the boss is vulnerable. Follow up with Genesis if all 4 Stains are available. Burn-Based Loop: Apply Burn with Wildfire \u2192 Trigger Thermal Transfer for AP gain \u2192 Chain into high-cost skills.\n\nWhy It\u2019s Best: Choralim is Lune\u2019s signature weapon, tailored for her elemental rhythm. Its level 10 and 20 passives enhance multi-hit performance and provide utility for AP regeneration and status cycling. Works best with Luminas like Energizing Turn and Pictos that reward fast turn cycling. How to Obtain: Found in Act 2 via exploration or side quests. Stats & Scaling: Max Power: 3390 | Element: Lightning | Scaling: Vitality (A), Agility (S) Why It Works: Kralim benefits Lune\u2019s elemental diversity. Its passives reward alternating between elements, enhancing AP recovery and debuff uptime. Pairs well with builds using skills like Ice Lance and Immolation in rotation. How to Obtain: Available early in Act 1 through story or side content. Stats & Scaling: Max Power: 3067 | Element: Lightning | Scaling: Vitality (S), Luck (A) Why It\u2019s Good Early: Trebuchim provides solid base power and survivability.\n\nExcellent nuke for endgame mobs or bosses. Thermal Transfer Low Ice damage. If the enemy is Burning, Lune gains 4 AP. With 2 Earth Stains, she gets a second turn. Best AP regeneration tool in her kit. Healing Light Restores HP and clears debuffs from an ally. Consuming 2 Earth Stains makes it free. Reliable support with minimal cost. Rebirth Revives an ally and grants AP. Requires 3 Lightning Stains to remove the AP cost. Must-have for late-game sustain. ... Openers: Start fights with Elemental Trick or Earth Rising to begin building your Stains pool. Mid-fight Utility: If allies are low or enemies are applying pressure, switch to Healing Light or Thermal Transfer for tempo recovery. Burst Phase: Use Hell or Lightning Dance when Stains align and the boss is vulnerable. Follow up with Genesis if all 4 Stains are available. Burn-Based Loop: Apply Burn with Wildfire \u2192 Trigger Thermal Transfer for AP gain \u2192 Chain into high-cost skills.\n\nFrom melting enemies with Hell, to restoring full party stability with Tree of Life, Lune rewards players who plan ahead and execute rotations carefully. Explore more build guides and team synergies for Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 in our full coverage here. All Pictos & Where to Get Them \u2013 Part 1: Early Game \u00b7 All Pictos & Where to Get Them \u2013 Part 2: Mid-Game \u00b7 Best Endgame Pictos & Build Combos in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 (Final Guide \u2013 Part 3) Ultimate Pictos Guide in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u00b7 All 33 Music Record Locations in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u2013 Connoisseur Achievement Guide \u00b7 All Lost Gestrals Locations and Rewards \u2013 Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 Guide \u00b7 Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u2013 All Paint Cage Locations and Rewards Guide \u00b7 Mastering Gradient Attacks and Counters in Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u00b7 Ultimate Beginner\u2019s Guide for Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 \u2013 10 Tips to Start Strong \u00b7\n\nIn the world of Clair Obscur: Expedition 33, Lune stands out as one of the most flexible characters for both new and experienced players. Whether you\u2019re looking for the best Lune build as a high-impact damage dealer or a supportive elemental mage, her toolkit allows for exceptional versatility. Her design embraces Clair Obscur\u2019s unique \u201cStains\u201d system, rewarding tactical play and deliberate skill usage. With access to a variety of elemental skills\u2014including flame-based nukes and ice-based control options\u2014Lune\u2019s playstyle can be adapted for burst DPS, long-term elemental damage, or team utility. Unlike some characters who excel only in niche roles, Lune builds scale well throughout the campaign. Her ability to apply Burn and Mark status effects supports allies like Maelle and Sciel, making her a linchpin in many optimal early- and mid-game team compositions.",
