    "thinking": "Good results. Let me synthesize Lune's best six skills and endgame viability.\n\nThe core endgame skills that appear consistently:\n- Lightning Dance (primary nuke, requires Fire + Ice + Earth stains)\n- Elemental Genesis (AoE nuke, requires one of each element)\n- Hell (AoE burn + damage, opens stain generation)\n- Wildfire (AoE burn, stain generation)\n- Elemental Trick (generates stains, Ice damage)\n- Terraquake (Earth damage, break, stain generation - replaces Crustal Crush)\n- Ice Lance (replaces Thermal Transfer in some builds - Ice damage + slow + stain)\n\n\n- Thermal Transfer (AP generation when enemy burning)\n- Crippling Tsunami (AoE slow + Ice damage)\n\nSo the real question is whether Lune actually fits into my planned endgame team of Maelle/Sciel/Verso. Sources confirm she's viable endgame, but Sciel is widely considered the superior support, so she'd likely replace Verso instead. On the weapon front, Game8 recommends Choralim for Act 3 since its passives synergize well with Pictos.\n\nturn generation, though Kralim is also highly regarded\u2014and I've already got both in inventory at usable levels, so this choice will shape my skill priorities going forward.",
