    "type": "text",
    "text": "**Endgame party viability first:** Yes, Lune sees significant endgame use \u2014 she's described as an endgame nuker with explosive elemental burst, capable of turn looping with Cheater and massive AoE with Hell and Genesis. However, the standard consensus team is Maelle/Sciel/Verso, with Lune as the main alternative if you want more AoE or a Kralim-based loop build. She'd typically replace Sciel (trading support for damage) or slot into a different team composition entirely.\n\n**Best six skills** \u2014 sources converge on this core set for Kralim endgame:\n\n1. **Lightning Dance** \u2014 primary single-target nuke (requires Fire + Ice + Earth stains)\n2. **Elemental Genesis** \u2014 AoE version of the same; if fighting a group, build toward Genesis; single boss, go Lightning Dance\n3. **Hell** \u2014 cast Hell turn 1 to guarantee four stains and AoE burn, then Genesis or Lightning Dance turn 2\n4. **Elemental Trick** \u2014 stain generation + opener\n5. **Terraquake** \u2014 replaces Crustal Crush; helps break tough enemies while generating Earth stains\n6. **Wildfire** or **Ice Lance** \u2014 Ice Lance replaces Thermal Transfer in Act 3 because it generates stains, which Thermal Transfer cannot; Wildfire is the alternative if you want AoE burn application\n\n**One complication worth flagging:** sources diverge on her endgame weapon. Kralim is widely praised, but Game8 recommends switching to Choralim for Act 3, whose passives synergise with Pictos that grant extra turns and with multi-hit skills at high crit rate. You have both in inventory per the overview file, so this is worth investigating \u2014 skill priorities shift somewhat depending on which you use.",
