Weesper Neon Flow that works system-wide, offline, and across all your apps. ... Claude's voice feature sends audio to Anthropic's servers for processing.\n\nClaude AI voice mode is a conversational interface. You speak to the AI, the AI speaks back. It is comparable to asking a highly intelligent assistant a question out loud. This is powerful for reasoning, summarising, and generating ideas \u2014 but it is a fundamentally different workflow from professional dictation. ... System-wide text insertion \u2014 dictated text appears wherever your cursor is: emails, documents, chat apps, code editors, web forms \u00b7 Long-form transcription \u2014 uninterrupted capture of 2, 5, or 20 minutes of speech into a single document \u00b7 Offline capability \u2014 transcription continues without an internet connection, on a plane, in a hospital, or behind a corporate firewall \u00b7 Privacy guarantees \u2014 audio never leaves your device \u00b7 Multilingual support \u2014 professionals worldwide work in their native language \u00b7 Claude AI voice mode satisfies none of these requirements in its current form.\n\nYou can explore this workflow in detail in our guide to voice-first AI workflows with Claude and ChatGPT. One aspect that professionals ask about frequently: where does Claude process your voice data? Claude\u2019s voice feature sends audio to Anthropic\u2019s servers. The text-to-speech component uses ElevenLabs technology, which Anthropic lists as a subcontractor in its terms of service. This means your spoken content passes through at minimum two external services before you receive a response. For casual questions and general productivity tasks, this is an entirely reasonable trade-off. For dictating confidential client information, protected health information, or legally privileged communications, the cloud architecture introduces compliance and confidentiality concerns. This is one reason many compliance-conscious organisations adopt offline dictation for the 